./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_global/jd_texts/05_nvidia_solution_architect_generative_ai_data_and_post_training.md:10:NVIDIA’s Worldwide Field Operations (WWFO) team is looking for a SolutionsArchitect with deep expertise Generative AI post-training from data processingto model alignment, with a strong background in Large Language Models (LLMs). Inparticular, we are seeking someone skilled in data preparation and curation forlarge-scale model training, as well as in LLM alignment techniques such asreinforcement learning from human feedback (RLHF) and Supervised Finetuning(SFT).In this role, you will operate at the intersection of innovative AI research andreal-world applications. You will work as the primary technical specialist forNVIDIA customers, helping drive innovation powered by NVIDIA’s hardware andsoftware platform. You will develop proof-of-concept solutions, demonstrateadvanced neural network architectures, and help customers adapt and optimizefoundation models using NVIDIA technologies for their specific domains. A keypart of this role involves close collaboration with a wide range of team membersincluding developers, data scientists, IT managers, and senior executives.The ideal candidate is an experienced AI specialist with a solid foundation inLLMs and expertise across data processing techniques including large scale datacuration, cleaning and Synthetic Data Generation. The candidate should haveconfirmed experience in Large-Scale post-training using supervised fine-tuningand/or Reinforcement Learning techniques. Hands-on experience applyingtechniques related to reinforcement learning for LLM alignment is a nice tohave.What You Will Be Doing * Serve as the primary technical expert to NVIDIA's customers, understanding their technology and providing guidance on post training process in terms of tools and methodology. * Build proof-of-concepts and demonstrations that highlight the power of NVIDIA AI platforms applied to LLMs post training. * Partner with developers, researchers, technology specialists, IT professionals, and executives to facilitate the integration of NVIDIA technology. * Partner with Engineering, Product and Sales teams to develop, plan best suitable solutions for customers. Enable development and growth of product features through customer feedback and proof-of-concept evaluations. What We Need To See * MS/PhD or equivalent experience in Computer Science, Data Science, Electrical/Computer Engineering, Physics, Mathematics, other Engineering fields. * Deep expertise in AI/Deep Learning, with hands-on experience in training and finetuning LLMs. * Expertise with deep learning frameworks for training LLMs (PyTorch, Megatron-LM, Nemo, Transformers, TRL, VeRL) * Excellent verbal, written communication, and technical presentation skills in English. * 6+ years' work or research experience with Python/ C++ / other software development * AI passionate with a growth mindset, ability to collaborate effectively with different teams (Engineering, Product, Sales, Marketing) in a rapid evolving environment while continuously learning and sharing insights. Ways To Stand Out From The Crowd * Familiarity with NVIDIA Nemo Collection (Nemo-Curator, Nemo-RL, Megatron-Bridge). * Track record in data processing as well as running LLM training and customization with Reinforcement Learning approaches. * Understanding of HPC systems: data center architecture high speed interconnect InfiniBand, Cluster Storage and Scheduling related design and/or management experience. Widely considered to be one of the technology world’s most desirable employers,NVIDIA offers highly competitive salaries and a comprehensive benefits package.As you plan your future, see what we can offer www.nvidiabenefits.com/NVIDIA is committed to fostering a diverse work environment and proud to be anequal opportunity employer. As we highly value diversity in our current andfuture employees, we do not discriminate (including in our hiring and promotionpractices) on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender,gender expression, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status,disability status or any other characteristic protected by law.JR2008246Show more Show less
./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_global/jd_texts/10_cognitivo_ag_ai_architect_mwd.md:10:Als Unternehmensberatung für Software und Analytics unterstützt die cognitivo AGmit intelligenten IT- und Branchenlösungen sowie fachlich fundierterstrategischer Beratung. Mit unserer Kompetenz im Bereich Software und Analyticstragen wir dazu bei, Prozesse zu optimieren, neue Geschäftsmodelle zu entwickelnund den Weg in Zeiten der digitalen Transformation zu ebnen.Wir sind seit vielen Jahren ein gefragter Partner von Versicherungen, Banken undFinanzdienstleister und suchen aktuell einen erfahrenen AI Architect (m/w/d),der unser Team verstärkt.Aufgaben * Du bist verantwortlich für die Konzeption und Entwicklung einer innovativen Softwarearchitektur, die auf RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) und MCP (Multi-Chain Processing) basierenden KI-Agentensysteme unterstützt. Dabei sorgen Sie für eine effiziente Strukturierung und Integration der Komponenten, um die Leistungsfähigkeit und Skalierbarkeit der Systeme sicherzustellen * Du erforschst und entwickelst neue Methoden und Ansätze, um die Grenzen großer Sprachmodelle zu erweitern. Ziel ist es, die Fähigkeiten der Modelle zu verbessern und ihre Einsatzmöglichkeiten in komplexen Anwendungsfällen zu erweitern * Du wählst geeignete Large Language Models (LLMs), wie beispielsweise OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini und andere, aus und integrierst diese in die bestehende Systemarchitektur. Zudem bindest Du verschiedene Agentic-Frameworks, wie LangChain, AutoGen, CrewAI, LlamaIndex, PydanticAI oder Agno, ein, um die Funktionalität der KI-Agenten zu erweitern * Du baust Agentic-Reasoning-Mechanismen sowie RAG-Pipelines auf, bspw. auf Basis von Tools wie PromptFlow, LangGraph oder ähnlichen Frameworks. Dabei entwickelst Du Verfahren, die es den KI-Agenten ermöglichen, komplexe Aufgaben durch reasoning und retrieval-gestützte Prozesse effizient zu bewältigen * Du orchestrierst die Integration und den Ablauf verschiedener Tools und Komponenten, um komplexe Multi-Chain Processing (MCP) und Agent-Flows zu steuern und zu optimieren. Dabei stellst Du sicher, dass alle Komponenten nahtlos zusammenarbeiten und die gewünschten Ergebnisse erzielen * Du führst eine methodische Evaluation der entwickelten KI-Systeme durch, um ihre Leistungsfähigkeit, Zuverlässigkeit und Effizienz zu messen. Dabei verwendest Du geeignete Testverfahren und Metriken, um die Qualität der Systeme kontinuierlich zu verbessern Qualifikation * Nachweisbare Erfahrung als Software Architect, Solution Architect oder in einer vergleichbaren Rolle, idealerweise mit Fokus auf KI/ML-Systeme * Tiefgehendes Verständnis von modernen KI-Architekturen, insbesondere Generative AI, Large Language Models (LLMs), Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG), Vektor-Datenbanken, Model Context Protocol (MCP) und Agent-to-Agent-Kommunikation (A2A). * Fundierte Kenntnisse in der Softwareentwicklung und im Design verteilter Systeme (on premise) * Du hast ein gutes Verständnis von Daten-Engineering-Prinzipien und Datenbanktechnologien (SQL, Vector DBs) * Ausgeprägte konzeptionelle Fähigkeiten, strategisches Denken und die Fähigkeit, komplexe technische Sachverhalte verständlich zu kommunizieren * Du hast ein abgeschlossenes Studium oder PhD in der Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Mathematik, Physik oder einer verwandten Fachrichtung * Du bringst Begeisterung für Innovationen im KI-Bereich und die Gestaltung zukunftsweisender Lösungen mit * Hohe technische Kompetenz, das bedeutet, dass du in der Lage bist, komplexe Software zu entwickeln und produktionstauglich zu machen * Du arbeitest eigenverantwortliche und bringst gleichzeitig ein ausgeprägtes Teamverständnis. * Sehr gute Deutschkenntnisse auf C1-Niveau sind für diese Position unerlässlich Benefits * Kollegiale und familiäre Atmosphäre * Förderung der Teamkultur, Teamausflüge, Co-Working * Flache Hierarchien mit kurzen Entscheidungswegen * Spannende Projekte für große, internationale Unternehmen * Benefits (Edenredkarte, Jobrad, betriebliche Altersvorsorge, etc.) * Ein umfangreiches Weiterbildungsangebot * Moderne Software & Tools, Mobilität bei Projekteinsätzen * Unbefristeter Arbeitsvertrag mit attraktiver Vergütung und 30 Urlaubstage pro Jahr * Flexible Arbeitszeiten für die perfekte Work-Life-Balance Wir bieten Dir ein aufstrebendes und innovatives Arbeitsumfeld, in dem Du DeineFähigkeiten und Kenntnisse erweitern und weiterentwickeln kannst.Wenn Du eine Leidenschaft für die Gestaltung und Umsetzung hochwertigerSoftwarelösungen hast und gerne in einem Team arbeitest, freuen wir uns aufDeine Bewerbung.Interessiert? Dann freuen wir uns auf Deine Bewerbung!Show more Show less
./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_global/jd_texts/56_version_1_cloud_ai_solution_architect.md:10:Company DescriptionVersion 1 has celebrated over 29 years in Technology Services and continues tobe trusted by global brands to deliver solutions that drive customer success.Our expertise enables our customers to navigate the rapidly changingDigital-First world we live in. We foster strong partnerships with leadingtechnology giants including Microsoft, AWS, Oracle, Red Hat, OutSystems,Snowflake, ensuring that our customers are provided with the highest qualitysolutions and services.We’re An Award-winning Employer Reflecting How Our Employees Are At The VeryHeart Of Version 1 And What We Do * UK & Ireland's premier AWS, Microsoft & Oracle partner * 3300+ strong, €350/£300m revenue business * 10+ years as a Great Place to Work in Ireland & UK * Best Workplace for Women in the UK & Ireland by GPTW * Best Workplace for Wellbeing in the UK by GPTW We’re a core values driven company, we hire people who share our values, and wereward those who display and foster them, it’s deeply embedded within our DNA.Invest in us and we’ll invest in you!Job DescriptionAs a Cloud / AI Solution Architect, you will lead the design and delivery ofscalable, secure, and cost-effective cloud-native and AI/ML solutions. This is adelivery-focused role, responsible for building PoCs, MVPs, and production-readyarchitectures that integrate AI capabilities into enterprise platforms. You willwork closely with cross-functional teams to ensure solutions meet businessobjectives, technical standards, and compliance requirements.Key Responsibilities * Architect and Deliver AI Solutions * Translate business requirements into end-to-end AI/ML architectures including data pipelines, model lifecycle, and MLOps. * Build and productionize PoCs and MVPs for AI use cases (including GenAI, LLMs, embeddings, RAG pipelines). * Cloud-Native Architecture * Design secure, scalable architectures on Azure and/or AWS using containers, serverless, API management, and event-driven patterns. * Implement multi-cloud and hybrid strategies where required. * Data Platforms & Integration * Develop data lakes, lakehouses, and warehouses using platforms like Databricks, Azure Synapse, Delta Lake. * Ensure data governance, lineage, and compliance (GDPR, ISO). * Automation & DevOps * Automate infrastructure using Terraform, Bicep, and implement CI/CD pipelines for apps and ML workflows. * Security & Governance * Apply best practices for identity, access, encryption, and compliance. * Maintain architecture documentation and ensure alignment with IT strategy. * Leadership & Collaboration * Guide developers, data scientists, and engineers through delivery phases. * Share best practices and create reusable accelerators for future projects. Qualifications * 10+ years in ICT infrastructure, cloud, and solution architecture. * Proven experience delivering AI/ML solutions from PoC to production. * Expertise in Azure and/or AWS cloud-native services, microservices, and API design. * Strong knowledge of MLOps, IaC (Terraform, Bicep), and CI/CD. * Experience with data platforms (Databricks, Synapse, Delta Lake) and governance. * Familiarity with GenAI, LLMs, vector search, and responsible AI practices. * Excellent communication and documentation skills. Additional InformationWhy Version 1?At Version 1, we believe in providing our employees with a comprehensivebenefits package that prioritises their wellbeing, professional growth, andfinancial stability. * Share in our success with our Quarterly Performance-Related Profit Share Scheme, where employees collectively benefit from a share of our company's profits. * Strong Career Progression & mentorship coaching through our Strength in Balance & Leadership schemes with a dedicated quarterly Pathways Career Development programme. * Flexible/remote working, Version 1 is tremendously understanding of life events and people’s individual circumstances and offer flexibility to help achieve a healthy work life balance. * Financial Wellbeing initiatives including; Pension, Private Healthcare Cover, Life Assurance, Financial advice and an Employee Discount scheme. * Employee Wellbeing schemes including Gym Discounts, Bike to Work, Fitness classes, Mindfulness Workshops, Employee Assistance Programme and much more. Generous holiday allowance, enhanced maternity/paternity leave, marriage/civil partnership leave and special leave policies. * Educational assistance, incentivised certifications, and accreditations, including AWS, Microsoft, Oracle, and Red Hat. * Reward schemes including Version 1’s Annual Excellence Awards & ‘Call-Out’ platform. * Environment, Social and Community First initiatives allow you to get involved in local fundraising and development opportunities as part of fostering our diversity, inclusion and belonging schemes. And many more exciting benefits… drop us a note to find out more.Ekta Bahl - Talent Acquisition Capability PartnerShow more Show less
./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_global/jd_texts/11_liztek_solution_architect_ai_mlops_lahore_onsite.md:10:Solution Architect AI & MLOps - Lahore (Onsite)Join our LinkedIn Liztek community:https://lnkd.in/gcbGihw9Summary:The Solution Architect for AI & MLOps will lead the design, development, anddeployment of scalable AI, machine learning, and MLOps solutions. This rolerequires deep technical expertise, strong architectural thinking, and theability to collaborate with cross‑functional teams to deliver enterprise‑gradeAI systems. The position is fully onsite in Lahore.Job Description:• Design end‑to‑end AI and MLOps architectures, including data pipelines, modeltraining workflows, deployment strategies, and monitoring frameworks.• Collaborate with data scientists, ML engineers, and software teams totranslate business requirements into scalable technical solutions.• Lead the implementation of MLOps best practices such as CI/CD for ML,automated model retraining, versioning, and governance.• Evaluate and select appropriate cloud services, tools, and frameworks for AIand ML workloads.• Ensure solutions meet performanceShow more Show less
./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_global/jd_texts/30_globallogic_ai_computer_vision_solution_architect_irc281985.md:10:DescriptionJoin GlobalLogic’s Architects Team within the Healthcare Business Unit,supporting clients across the EMEA region. This strategic role focuses onengaging new clients, designing advanced AI solutions for medical imageanalysis, and launching projects involving computer vision, deep learning, andgenerative AI. You’ll work on cutting-edge use cases like diagnostic assistance,surgical planning, and radiology automation, bringing meaningful impact topatient care. If you’re passionate about AI in healthcare and want to driveinnovation with real-world results, we’d love to hear from you.Requirements * Master’s or PhD in Computer Science, AI, Biomedical Engineering, or a related field. * 7+ years of experience in AI/ML with at least 4 years focused on computer vision and deep learning. * Proven experience with CNN architectures (e.g., ResNet, UNet, EfficientNet, VGG). * Experience with GANs (e.g., CycleGAN, StyleGAN, Pix2Pix) and synthetic image generation. * Hands-on with TensorFlow, PyTorch, OpenCV, and related vision libraries. * Strong understanding of preprocessing techniques for medical imaging data (e.g., DICOM, NIfTI). * Familiarity with training in cloud environments (Azure, AWS, GCP). * Experience in deploying models and integrating with PACS systems or cloud-native imaging stacks. * Solid understanding of model performance metrics and validation strategies for imaging. * Excellent communication skills and at least Upper-Intermediate English level. Preferred Qualifications (Nice To Have) * Experience with FDA/CE Class B or C medical imaging products. * Familiarity with explainable AI (Grad-CAM, LIME) and fairness techniques for imaging models. * Knowledge of FHIR, HL7, and healthcare data standards. * Understanding of HIPAA, GDPR, or other relevant data protection regulations. * Experience with AI for surgical robotics, augmented reality in healthcare, or histopathology image analysis. * Involvement in technical presales or client advisory initiatives. Job responsibilities * Design, develop, and optimize AI models for computer vision, segmentation, objects detection, image classification, etc. * Lead computer vision and AI solutioning in client engagements and presales discussions. * Build CNN- and GAN-based architectures tailored for healthcare and medical imaging use cases. * Prepare and preprocess large-scale datasets from modalities like X-ray, CT, MRI, and digital pathology. * Guide annotation strategies and quality control for labeled data. * Collaborate with cloud, DevOps, and QA teams to integrate models into production pipelines. * Ensure model robustness, explainability, and regulatory readiness (e.g., traceability, reproducibility). * Conduct technical workshops and communicate complex concepts to clients in an accessible way. * Stay current with research trends and evaluate new techniques for potential integration. * Contribute to internal accelerators, frameworks, and IP development. What we offerCulture of caring. At GlobalLogic, we prioritize a culture of caring. Acrossevery region and department, at every level, we consistently put people first.From day one, you’ll experience an inclusive culture of acceptance andbelonging, where you’ll have the chance to build meaningful connections withcollaborative teammates, supportive managers, and compassionate leaders.Learning and development. We are committed to your continuous learning anddevelopment. You’ll learn and grow daily in an environment with manyopportunities to try new things, sharpen your skills, and advance your career atGlobalLogic. With our Career Navigator tool as just one example, GlobalLogicoffers a rich array of programs, training curricula, and hands-on opportunitiesto grow personally and professionally.Interesting & meaningful work. GlobalLogic is known for engineering impact forand with clients around the world. As part of our team, you’ll have the chanceto work on projects that matter. Each is a unique opportunity to engage yourcuriosity and creative problem-solving skills as you help clients reimaginewhat’s possible and bring new solutions to market. In the process, you’ll havethe privilege of working on some of the most cutting-edge and impactfulsolutions shaping the world today.Balance and flexibility. We believe in the importance of balance andflexibility. With many functional career areas, roles, and work arrangements,you can explore ways of achieving the perfect balance between your work andlife. Your life extends beyond the office, and we always do our best to help youintegrate and balance the best of work and life, having fun along the way!High-trust organization. We are a high-trust organization where integrity iskey. By joining GlobalLogic, you’re placing your trust in a safe, reliable, andethical global company. Integrity and trust are a cornerstone of our valueproposition to our employees and clients. You will find truthfulness, candor,and integrity in everything we do.About GlobalLogicGlobalLogic, a Hitachi Group Company, is a trusted digital engineering partnerto the world’s largest and most forward-thinking companies. Since 2000, we’vebeen at the forefront of the digital revolution – helping create some of themost innovative and widely used digital products and experiences. Today wecontinue to collaborate with clients in transforming businesses and redefiningindustries through intelligent products, platforms, and services.Show more Show less
./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_global/jd_texts/08_vaporvm_principal_ai_data_solutions_architect.md:10:We are seeking a highly accomplished Principal AI & Data Solutions Architect tolead the end-to-end design, architecture, and delivery of enterprise-scale DataScience, AI, Machine Learning, and Advanced Analytics solutions. This roledemands deep technical expertise, strategic thinking, and strong client-facingleadership to translate complex business challenges into scalable, secure, andhigh-impact AI solutions.Key ResponsibilitiesSolution Architecture & Design * Lead the end-to-end architecture of advanced AI, machine learning, and data science solutions across cloud and hybrid environments. * Design scalable, secure, and resilient data pipelines for ingestion, transformation, feature engineering, model training, deployment, and monitoring. * Define solution blueprints, reference architectures, architecture diagrams, and best-practice frameworks aligned with enterprise and regulatory standards. * Architect modern analytics platforms using Microsoft Fabric (Lakehouse, Data Factory, Synapse, OneLake) for unified data and analytics workloads. * Recommend and govern technology stacks spanning cloud platforms, data platforms, ML frameworks, and visualization tools.Technical Leadership & Governance * Provide technical leadership and mentorship to data scientists, ML engineers, data engineers, and BI teams. * Review, validate, and approve AI/ML models and data architectures for performance, scalability, security, explainability, and compliance. * Establish and enforce MLOps, DataOps, and DevOps best practices, including CI/CD pipelines and model lifecycle management. * Ensure solutions are cloud-native, cost-optimized, and production-ready, meeting enterprise SLAs and governance standards.Client & Stakeholder Engagement * Partner with senior business and technical stakeholders to translate business requirements into robust technical architectures. * Lead architecture discussions, technical workshops, design reviews, and executive-level presentations. * Develop and present solution roadmaps, architecture proposals, and technical documentation to decision-makers. * Act as a trusted advisor, guiding clients on AI strategy, data modernization, and analytics transformation.Implementation & Delivery Excellence * Oversee the deployment of machine learning models, data pipelines, and analytics solutions into production environments. * Ensure strong alignment between solution design, implementation, and measurable business outcomes. * Lead troubleshooting and resolution of complex data, AI, and performance challenges in large-scale environments. * Drive continuous improvement in solution quality, reliability, and operational efficiency.Required Skills & Qualifications * 6–10+ years of experience in Data Science, Machine Learning, AI Engineering, or Advanced Analytics. * 3+ years in a Solution Architect / AI Architect / ML Architect role.Core Technical Expertise * Machine Learning & AI: TensorFlow, PyTorch, Scikit-learn * Data Engineering: Apache Spark, Databricks, Kafka, Airflow * Cloud Platforms: Microsoft Azure (preferred), AWS, and/or GCP * MLOps: MLflow, Kubeflow, Azure ML, SageMaker, Vertex AI * Modern Analytics & BI: * Microsoft Fabric (Lakehouse, Data Factory, Synapse, OneLake) * Power BI (enterprise reporting, semantic models, DAX, performance optimization) * Databases: * Microsoft SQL Server * MySQL * Strong understanding of data architecture, distributed systems, data modeling, and governance frameworks. * Exceptional communication skills with the ability to simplify complex technical concepts for executive audiences. * Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Data Science, AI, or a related field.Show more Show less
./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_global/jd_texts/63_delphi_consulting_middle_east_ai_architect.md:10:Join Delphi - Where Innovation meets transformationAt Delphi, we believe in creating an environment where our people thrive. Ourhybrid work model empowers you to choose where you work—whether it's from theoffice, your home, or a mix of both— so you can prioritize what matters most. Weare committed to supporting your personal goals, family, and overall well- beingwhile driving transformative results for our clients.We welcome exceptional talent from anywhere across the globe. Interviews andonboarding are conducted virtually, reflecting our digital-first mindset.Rooted in the region, we specialize in delivering tailored, impactful solutionsin Data, Advanced Analytics and AI, Infrastructure, Cloud Security, andApplication Modernization. Whether it’s enabling predictive analytics,transforming operations with automation, or driving customer engagement withintelligent platforms, we are the trusted partner for organizations ready toembrace a smarter, more efficient future.About the RoleAI/ML Technical Architect – Generative AI & Agentic SystemsLocation: DubaiWe are seeking a Senior AI/ML Solution Architect with deep expertise inGenerative AI and agentic systems to lead the architecture and delivery ofenterprise-scale AI solutions. This role requires a strong combination ofhands-on technical capability across Large Language Models (LLMs) and SmallLanguage Models (SLMs), along with the architectural leadership to design,integrate, and deploy AI systems across cloud, edge, and on-premisesenvironments.The successful candidate will architect scalable agentic platforms, buildadvanced RAG and fine-tuning pipelines, and design robust integration frameworksconnecting AI services with enterprise applications. This role sits at the coreof AI transformation initiatives, balancing cutting-edge innovation withproduction-grade engineering, performance optimization, and security-firstdesign.Experience Requirements * 8+ years of experience in software engineering, data, or AI systems * 2+ years of hands-on experience with Generative AI and LLM-based solutions * 4+ years of experience designing and architecting enterprise-scale platforms and distributed systemsKey ResponsibilitiesArchitecture & System Design * Architect scalable agentic systems using advanced LLM and SLM capabilities * Design multi-agent orchestration frameworks for complex, automated workflows * Define context, memory, and state-management architectures for persistent agent interactions * Implement Model Context Protocol (MCP)–based integrations across enterprise servicesAI & Platform Implementation * Design and optimize Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) architectures * Build agent solutions using LangChain, LangGraph, Semantic Kernel, Agno, and custom frameworks * Architect and deploy model inference pipelines across cloud, edge, and on-prem environments * Develop fine-tuning strategies for LLMs and SLMs, including domain and task specialization * Lead model compression, quantization, and performance-optimization initiativesIntegration & Enterprise Connectivity * Architect secure REST, gRPC, and GraphQL APIs for AI platform services * Design event-driven architectures using message buses and webhooks * Implement authentication and authorization systems (SSO, OIDC, token-based security) * Build and govern enterprise connectors (Slack, Jira, Salesforce, ERP/CRM platforms)Data, Models & Evaluation * Design data preprocessing and governance pipelines (cleaning, deduplication, PII handling) * Architect embedding generation, re-indexing, and retrieval optimization workflows * Define chunking, windowing, and content processing strategies * Establish model evaluation, benchmarking, and selection frameworksRequired Technical SkillsCore AI & GenAI * Deep experience with GPT-4, Claude, LLaMA, and enterprise/open-source LLM ecosystems * Expertise deploying and optimizing SLMs (Phi-3, Gemma, TinyLlama) * Advanced agent frameworks: LangChain, LangGraph, Semantic Kernel, Agno * RAG systems, vector databases, semantic and hybrid retrievalFine-Tuning & Model Optimization * Parameter-efficient tuning: LoRA, QLoRA, DoRA, AdaLoRA * Prompt-tuning, adapters, prefix tuning, P-tuning v2 * RLHF / RLAIF pipelines * Compression techniques: quantization (INT8/INT4, GPTQ, AWQ, GGML), pruning, distillationDeployment & Performance * Multi-environment deployment (cloud, edge, on-prem) * Autoscaling, rate-limiting, and resource governance * Real-time inference, streaming pipelines, adaptive reasoning controlEngineering & Platforms * TensorFlow, PyTorch, Hugging Face, LlamaIndex * API-driven system design and full-stack AI service development * AWS, Azure, GCP AI platforms * CI/CD, Docker, Kubernetes, monitoring and observabilityPreferred Qualifications * Master’s or PhD in Computer Science, AI, ML, or related field * Contributions to open-source AI projects or research publications * Experience with multi-modal and cross-modal systems * Strong grounding in MLOps and full model lifecycle management * Experience designing compliant and regulated AI systems * Demonstrated leadership in enterprise AI transformation programs * Cloud certifications (AWS, Azure, GCP – AI/ML focus)Technical Competencies Assessed * Distributed AI system architecture and design * Production code quality, scalability, and performance optimization * Model benchmarking, evaluation, and cost optimization * Security, privacy, and AI governance engineering * Enterprise-grade deployment and scaling strategiesWhat We Offer:At Delphi, we are dedicated to creating an environment where you can thrive,both professionally and personally. Our competitive compensation package,performance-based incentives, and health benefits are designed to ensure you'rewell-supported. We believe in your continuous growth and offer company-sponsored certifications, training programs, and skill-building opportunities tohelp you succeed. We foster a culture of inclusivity and support, with remotework options and a fully supported work-from- home setup to ensure your comfortand productivity. Our positive and inclusive culture includes team activities,wellness and mental health programs to ensure you feel supported.Show more Show less
