./data/eval/raw/head_of_ai_global/jd_texts/50_everai_senior_devops_engineer_full_remote_austria.md:10:Our Vision & Products🚀 EverAI — Building the Future of AI CompanionshipOne of the Top 15 Largest & Fastest-Growing AI Companies in the World35+ Million Users in 2 years — Help Us Reach 100M first, 500M nextAt EverAI, we’re shaping what it means to connect with AI. With 35+ millionusers and counting, we're not just building products — we're creating entirelynew categories.Our flagship product is the world’s largest AI girlfriend/boyfriend platform,redefining relationships for millions. It is governed by our proprietarymoderation system, EverGuard — an internal AI designed to ensure everything webuild is safe, ethical, and human-first.And we’re only just getting started!Our TeamWe are an enthusiastic, passionate and hardworking team of 70 people. Ourfounding team has strong entrepreneurial experience building and scaling webproducts from 0 to IPO.Alexis Soulopoulos [CEO] * 10+ years in Tech Executive Leadership * Co-Founder Mad Paws Holdings (from 0 to IPO) * Forbes 30 under 30 + Deloitte TechFast50 ’22 & ‘23 Michael Monin [Co-founder & CTO] * 10+ years as CTO / COO (web2/web3), 1+ year in AI/LLM * Serial-entrepreneur: MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue) and Zipchat (AI Chatbot for E-commerce brands) Thomas Lacroix [Co-founder & CMO] * 8+ years in Customer Acquisition & E-commerce Growth * Serial-entrepreneur: Curatible (sold to Blackstone) and MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue) Maruša Fasano [CFO/Legal] * 25+ years in Finance, Strategy, M&A * Ex-CFO/M&A @Curatible (exited to Blackstone) * Ex-President of the Board @SotremoSA (exited) * Co-founder/CFO @SoftOne (exited) Your RoleOur user base and tech team are expanding rapidly, we are therefore hiring aSenior DevOps Engineer to help us build and scale our platform and support ourengineering teams. You’ll have the opportunity to help define our roadmap andfind the best technical solutions to help our customers. You will also have timeto run some experiments and bring new ideas to the table.Reporting directly to our DevOps Lead, Mate, you will be responsible for: * Interacting with the engineers to provide infrastructure support * Manage, monitor and scale our existing services * Provision infrastructure and platform services through Infrastructure-as-Code, code reviews and testing You will be working with Michael (Co-founder & CTO), along with the Product teamand the Engineering team (web developers, SRE, data scientists).Your QualificationsMust-haves💼 5+ years of experience: * Public cloud, Kubernetes, GitOps * Observability through logs, metrics and tracing * Infrastucture-as-Code, Terraform, Helm * Ability to read and understand application code (Go, Python, shell) * In tech startups or any similarly agile and fast-paced environment 🗣 Strong communication & collaborative skills (perfectly fluent in English)🎯 Goal-oriented, ownership and commitment⚡️ Doer mindset - we are moving fast and need people who can balance execution,planning, and strategy🧢 Humble - willing to learn, open to feedback🫶🏻 User-centricity - you are proud of what you build and you share ourobsession for amazing user experience🍭 #NSFW - you are comfortable building products that are based on uncensoredmodels and contentBonus points * Past experience and/or interest in data science and generative AI (NLP, ML, MLOps, etc.) * Location: you must be able to work within ±4 CET Why EverAI?📈 Exponential Growth: From 35M+ users in 2 years, to 100M next — and 500Mbeyond🚀 Track Record of Category-Creating Innovation: We consistently launchworld-first AI applications — setting the pace, not following it🌍 Global Impact: Top-tier user growth, real-world adoption, and culturalrelevance🧠 Proven Leadership: A senior team that’s launched, scaled, and exited & IPO’dmultiple scale ups — now fully focused on reshaping AI companionship👥 Elite Remote Team: 100% remote and built to win — world-class talent fromTier 1 tech companies, with a culture of ownership, velocity, and radicalcreativity🛡️ Ethical Core: Our AI ecosystem is governed by EverGuard, our proprietary AImoderation technology, ensuring responsible development at scaleWhat we offer✍️ Contract Type: We prefer B2B, but we’re flexible, what matters is long-termcommitment and impact📍 Work From Anywhere: Fully remote. Choose the environment where you do yourbest work🏝️ Paid Time Off: 4 weeks (20 working days) of PTO per year to recharge andreset👨👩👧👦 Annual Gathering: A yearly in-person meetup to connect, brainstorm,and celebrate wins together❤️🩹 Health & Wellness Support: Up to $200 per year for wellbeing expenses +unlimited 1:1 sessions with psychologists and lifestyle experts through OpenUp(also available for up to three family members)🏢 Co-Working Space Budget: Work from a co-working space up to twice per month(35 EUR / 40 USD per visit) to stay inspired and connected📚 Learning Budget: Dedicated funds to support your professional growth:courses, books, conferences, events, or certifications💻 Equipment: Company laptop provided + monitor budget up to $250 for yourworkspace setup⚡ AI Tools Access: Premium access to ChatGPT, Cursor, Hugging Face, and others,to power your ideas and workflows🎯 Top Tier Talent Is Our MultiplierWe’re a fully remote group of A-players from Tier 1 tech, led by an exec teamwho’ve launched, scaled, and exited multiple companies. We move fast, and caredeeply about what we build — and who we build it with.We’re looking for exceptional talent ready to ship & distribute world-first AIproducts at scale, fast, and co-create with us this category-defining business.If that’s you — reach out and apply!💡 External Referral ProgramKnow someone who could be a great fit for this role? You can refer them throughthe EverAI External Referral Program and earn a bonus of up to $2,500 if they’rehired. Submit a referral here.Show more Show less
./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_global/jd_texts/16_sii_poland_ai_solution_architect_fmx.md:10:We are looking for an AI Solution Architect with a comprehensive understandingof AI technologies, including classical machine learning, deep learning, andrecent advancements in generative AI. The role requires a strong grasp of thebenefits and limitations of AI models and algorithms, with the ability toidentify opportunities where they can solve real-world challenges effectively. Akey responsibility will be evaluating the feasibility of AI solutions andoutlining the necessary steps for their successful implementation. This positionmay involve up to 50% of time spent on non-technical activities such as businessmeetings or sales support. Join us now!Sii ensures that all employment-related decisions are made solely on the basisof qualifications and competencies. We are committed to equal treatment of allindividuals, regardless of any protected characteristics, and promoting adiverse and inclusive work environment.Your tasks * Create AI system architectures that integrate machine learning models, data pipelines, and infrastructure requirements * Select appropriate AI models, fine-tune algorithms, and develop strategies for improving model performance, accuracy, and efficiency * Work closely with data scientists, engineers, product managers, and stakeholders to translate technical capabilities into actionable business solutions * Stay current with cutting-edge AI research, experimental techniques, and emerging technologies to drive continuous innovation in AI architecture * Develop technical presentations, and lead customer-facing meetings to demonstrate solution potential, address technical inquiries, and articulate AI value propositions to potential clients * Conduct comprehensive stakeholder interviews, facilitate discovery workshops, and systematically document detailed business requirements, technical constraints, and success criteria to define precise project scope and AI solution specifications Requirements * At least 5 years of experience developing customer-facing AI solutions, preferably with at least 2 years in a similar role * Advanced technical expertise in AI technologies (including models, algorithms, and tools) with comprehensive knowledge of at least one major cloud provider's AI/ML services (AWS, GCP, or Azure) * Strong cross-functional collaboration skills to translate complex cloud-based AI capabilities into actionable business solutions * Continuous learning mindset with current awareness of cloud AI technologies, including emerging services and machine learning infrastructure options * Capability to assess AI solution feasibility across cloud environments, understanding architectural trade-offs, cost implications, and performance optimization strategies * Fluent Polish required * Residing in Poland required Job no. 260107-955PRBenefits For YouGreat Place to WorkSolid financial situationContracts with the biggest brandsCentre of internal trainingsMany experts you can learn fromOpen and accessible management teamProfit sharingPassion Sponsorship programRegular integration events and tripsComfortable and well-equipped officesMySii appMedical careShow more Show less
./data/eval/blueprints/debug/staff_ai_engineer_global/20260415_174055/attempt_01_initial_raw_output.txt:1:{"meta":{"category_id":"staff_ai_engineer_global","category_name":"Staff AI Engineer — Global/Remote","macro_family":"ai_engineering_adjacent","priority":"secondary_target","confidence":"high","total_jobs":25,"deep_analysis_count":20,"low_sample_mode":false,"noisy_title_mode":false,"uncertainty_note":"Evidence is usable and not sparse: 25 jobs with high confidence. This behaves like a senior IC architecture category with a meaningful player-coach slice, not a formal people-management or research category."},"category_signature":{"one_sentence_summary":"Hands-on Staff/Principal AI Engineers in this market are hired to architect and productionize AI platforms and distributed systems, prove reliability and integration depth, and influence peers without overstating formal management.","distinctive_signals":["Architecture proof dominates: platform design appears in 24/25 roles (96%), with greenfield or mixed greenfield/optimization scope in 20/25 sampled roles.","The role is senior IC first: senior_ic is 25/25 (100%), with scope split between IC 14/25 (56%) and player-coach 11/25 (44%).","AI demand centers on shipped systems, not research: agent orchestration 12/25 (48%), RAG 9/25 (36%), guardrails/governance 7/25 (28%), while requires_phd_pct and research_heavy_pct are both 0/25 (0%)."],"citations":["Platform design 24/25 (96%); greenfield_split both 12 and greenfield 8 out of 25.","Seniority distribution senior_ic 25/25 (100%); role scope IC 14/25 (56%) and player_coach 11/25 (44%).","AI stack signals: agents_orchestration 12/25 (48%), RAG 9/25 (36%), guardrails_governance 7/25 (28%); disqualifiers requires_phd_pct 0/25 (0%) and research_heavy_pct 0/25 (0%)."]},"headline_pattern":{"recommended_structure":"[Staff|Principal] AI/ML Engineer | AI Platform Architecture, Distributed Systems, Production GenAI","safe_title_families":["Staff AI Engineer","Principal AI Engineer","Staff Software Engineer, AI/ML","Principal Engineer, Generative AI","Staff/Principal Software Engineer"],"safe_title_variants":["Principal AI Engineer","Staff Software Engineer, AI/ML","Principal Engineer, Generative AI","Principal Software Engineer","Staff Software Engineer"],"avoid_title_variants":["Head of AI","Director of AI Engineering","VP Engineering","AI Engineering Manager","Research Scientist"],"evidence_first_rules":["Use Staff/Principal framing first because title families cluster around principal_engineer 13/25 (52%) and staff_engineer 11/25 (44%).","Put architecture and production scope before tool names because platform design appears in 24/25 roles (96%) and no hard skill exceeds Python at 8/25 (32%).","Add AI/ML, Generative AI, agent, or RAG wording only when shipped work is documented; agents_orchestration appears in 12/25 (48%) and RAG in 9/25 (36%), not in every role.","Reserve leadership wording for technical influence, mentoring, and standards-setting; player_coach is 11/25 (44%), org_building 9/25 (36%), but hiring is only 2/25 (8%)."],"citations":["Title families: principal_engineer 13/25 (52%), staff_engineer 11/25 (44%), tech_lead 1/25 (4%).","Hard skills: Python leads at 8/25 (32%), distributed systems 7/25 (28%), observability 6/25 (24%).","Role scope and management: player_coach 11/25 (44%), org_building 9/25 (36%), hiring 2/25 (8%)."]},"tagline_profile_angle":{"positioning_angle":["Architecture-first senior IC who ships production AI platforms and distributed backend systems.","Player-coach technical leader who improves reliability, delivery quality, and cross-functional execution without relying on formal management claims."],"foreground":["Platform architecture and system design for AI/backend systems.","Production delivery of agent orchestration, RAG, evaluation, and guardrails when true.","Reliability, observability, and incident-aware productionization.","Cross-functional collaboration and mentoring with concrete delivery outcomes."],"avoid":["People-management-first positioning.","Provider-brand-heavy taglines without shipped platform evidence.","Research, publication, or PhD-style framing.","Consumer-scale or multi-cloud breadth claims without explicit metrics and scope."],"safe_positioning":["Show architecture ownership, integration depth, and production reliability because architecture is the strongest evidence type in 20 deep-analysis samples and platform design appears in 24/25 roles (96%).","Show collaboration and mentoring as force multipliers because collaboration appears in 23/25 roles (92%) and mentoring in 12/25 (48%).","Show AI delivery through shipped systems, evaluation, and guardrails because agents_orchestration appears in 12/25 (48%), RAG in 9/25 (36%), evaluation_quality in 5/25 (20%), and guardrails_governance in 7/25 (28%)."],"unsafe_positioning":["Do not imply direct hiring authority or formal people management unless the CV proves it; hiring appears in 2/25 roles (8%) and performance management in 1/25 (4%).","Do not imply research-heavy credentials; research_heavy_pct and requires_phd_pct are both 0/25 (0%).","Do not claim direct MCP, OpenAI, Anthropic, HIPAA, or full multi-cloud implementation unless explicitly documented; these are named in unsafe_claims_top despite low direct frequency."],"citations":["Soft skills: collaboration 23/25 (92%), mentoring 12/25 (48%), communication 10/25 (40%).","AI stack: agents_orchestration 12/25 (48%), RAG 9/25 (36%), evaluation_quality 5/25 (20%), guardrails_governance 7/25 (28%).","Management and disqualifiers: hiring 2/25 (8%), performance_management 1/25 (4%), research_heavy_pct 0/25 (0%), requires_phd_pct 0/25 (0%)."]},"core_competency_themes":[{"section_name":"Architecture And Platforms","themes":[{"theme":"AI platform architecture and system design","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This category is architecture-led. Show end-to-end design ownership for production systems, reusable platforms, and integration boundaries because platform design appears in 24/25 roles (96%) and architecture is the top valued evidence type in 20 deep-analysis samples.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: platform architecture, system design, AI platform. Use 2-3 mentions across headline/profile/experience/skills. Secondary keywords: greenfield, modernization. Use 1-2 mentions. Niche vendor names once only.","citation":"Platform design 24/25 (96%); valued evidence type architecture 20 deep-analysis samples."},{"theme":"Distributed systems and cloud-native backend foundations","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This market still screens for deep backend and distributed systems judgment under the AI layer. Show service boundaries, event-driven systems, APIs, and scalable backend delivery because distributed systems appears in 7/25 roles (28%) and backend engineering, CI/CD, and Kubernetes each appear in 4/25 (16%).","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: distributed systems, backend engineering. Use 2-3 mentions. Secondary keywords: event-driven systems, cloud-native systems, Kubernetes, CI/CD. Use 1-2 mentions. Niche language or cloud terms once only.","citation":"Hard skills: distributed systems 7/25 (28%), backend engineering 4/25 (16%), CI/CD 4/25 (16%), Kubernetes 4/25 (16%), event-driven systems 3/25 (12%), cloud-native systems 3/25 (12%)."},{"theme":"System integration and modernization under enterprise constraints","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"The hiring pain points point to integration complexity, modernization, and solution selection through POCs. Show cases where you connected AI or cloud services into existing enterprise systems and improved code quality or delivery safety.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: system integration, modernization, proof of concept, enterprise systems. Use 1-2 mentions. Niche domain terms once only and only if true.","citation":"Pain points are repeated as single-sample signals: integration across multiple systems (1), choose appropriate solutions through POCs (1), modernize and improve code quality while integrating AI services (1)."}]},{"section_name":"Production AI Delivery","themes":[{"theme":"Agent orchestration and reusable AI workflow systems","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"This category is more platform-and-orchestration oriented than generic LLM feature work. Show shipped agent workflows, reusable tool integrations, orchestration logic, and developer-facing enablement because agents_orchestration appears in 12/25 roles (48%).","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: agent orchestration, AI workflows. Use 2-3 mentions. Secondary keywords: developer tools, reusable platform, plugins. Use 1-2 mentions. Framework names only once and only if true.","citation":"AI stack signals: agents_orchestration 12/25 (48%); frameworks are fragmented, with LangChain highest at 5/25 (20%)."},{"theme":"RAG, retrieval, and vector-based grounding","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Retrieval-driven delivery is a visible category pattern, but not universal. Show grounded-answering systems, retrieval quality work, embeddings, and vector search only when you have production evidence because RAG appears in 9/25 (36%) and vector_search in 5/25 (20%).","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: RAG, retrieval, vector databases. Use 2-3 mentions for one or two core terms. Secondary keywords: embeddings, vector search. Use 1-2 mentions. Database brand names once only.","citation":"AI stack signals: RAG 9/25 (36%), vector_search 5/25 (20%); hard skills: vector databases 5/25 (20%), embeddings 4/25 (16%)."},{"theme":"Evaluation, guardrails, and production quality controls","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"This category values AI quality and safe production behavior more than generic prompt claims. Show eval harnesses, structured output validation, hallucination handling, guardrails, and governance where delivered because evaluation_quality appears in 5/25 (20%) and guardrails_governance in 7/25 (28%).","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: evaluation, guardrails, structured output validation, governance. Use 1-2 mentions. Niche compliance labels once only and only if directly supported.","citation":"AI stack signals: evaluation_quality 5/25 (20%), guardrails_governance 7/25 (28%); deep-analysis success metrics include handling hallucinations (1) and structured output validation (1)."}]},{"section_name":"Reliability And Operations","themes":[{"theme":"Reliability, observability, and production hardening","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"Production reliability is central to this category. Show uptime, incident reduction, latency stability, failure handling, and observability instrumentation because reliability is cited in 18 deep-analysis samples, observability appears in 6/25 roles (24%), and reliability is the top success metric cluster.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: reliability, observability, production. Use 2-3 mentions. Secondary keywords: incident response, SLOs, monitoring. Use 1-2 mentions only if you truly owned them. Tool names once only.","citation":"Valued evidence types: reliability 18 deep-analysis samples; hard skills: observability 6/25 (24%); success metrics: reliability appears 4 times, performance 3 times, scalability 2 times."},{"theme":"Cloud deployment and delivery discipline","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"Cloud and deployment tooling matter, but the sample does not support over-optimizing around one vendor. Show deployment rigor, containerization, and delivery systems when they are real, while keeping vendor claims narrow because multi_cloud appears in 8 samples, AWS in 4, and GCP in 2.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: AWS, GCP, Kubernetes, CI/CD. Use 1-2 mentions. Niche provider services once only. Do not force multi-cloud wording unless the CV proves more than one cloud.","citation":"Architecture cloud preference: multi_cloud 8 samples, AWS 4, GCP 2; hard skills: Kubernetes 4/25 (16%), CI/CD 4/25 (16%), cloud platforms 3/25 (12%)."},{"theme":"Security and governance for enterprise AI","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"A smaller but meaningful slice of roles asks for secure, governed AI delivery. Show practical controls, policy enforcement, or safe rollout processes when you implemented them because guardrails_governance appears in 7/25 (28%) and governance is a valued evidence type in 8 deep-analysis samples.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: security, governance, responsible AI. Use 1-2 mentions. Niche regulatory terms such as HIPAA or PHI once only and only if the CV proves that environment.","citation":"AI stack guardrails_governance 7/25 (28%); valued evidence type governance 8 deep-analysis samples; governance/compliance terms are individually low-frequency, with responsible AI highest at 2/25 (8%)."}]},{"section_name":"Technical Leadership And Influence","themes":[{"theme":"Cross-functional collaboration and stakeholder translation","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This market expects strong collaboration more consistently than any single hard skill. Show how you aligned product, platform, security, and engineering stakeholders around architecture and delivery because collaboration appears in 23/25 roles (92%) and communication in 10/25 (40%).","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: collaboration, stakeholder alignment, cross-functional. Use 2-3 mentions. Secondary keywords: communication, technical strategy. Use 1-2 mentions.","citation":"Soft skills: collaboration 23/25 (92%), communication 10/25 (40%)."},{"theme":"Mentoring and technical leadership without formal management inflation","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"There is a real player-coach signal, but not a people-manager signal. Show mentoring, standards-setting, reviews, and technical direction because mentoring appears in 12/25 roles (48%) and player_coach scope in 11/25 (44%), while hiring is only 2/25 (8%).","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: mentoring, technical leadership, standards. Use 1-2 mentions. Avoid manager, hiring, or org ownership terms unless explicitly evidenced.","citation":"Soft skills: mentoring 12/25 (48%), technical leadership 3/25 (12%); role scope player_coach 11/25 (44%); hiring 2/25 (8%)."},{"theme":"Org-building and standards as a scoped extension, not the headline","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"Some roles want senior engineers who help define standards or shape how teams build AI systems, but this should stay secondary to delivery. Include this only if you can show frameworks, standards, or internal enablement because org_building appears in 9/25 roles (36%).","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: engineering standards, enablement, internal platform. Use 1-2 mentions. Keep delivery metrics more prominent than process language.","citation":"Management_leadership org_building 9/25 (36%); deep-analysis unsafe claims warn against overstating people-management or company-wide ownership."}]}],"key_achievement_archetypes":[{"rank":1,"archetype":"Architected and shipped a production AI platform or gateway","what_it_proves":"Shows the core category value: architecture ownership, reusable platform thinking, and production delivery under reliability constraints.","pain_points_addressed":["need to define and drive ai technical strategy","need to build and scale advanced ai systems in production","need to establish ml engineering standards, security, and governance"],"metrics_to_include":["time to production","adoption by teams or users","supported workflows or integrations","reliability or availability","latency or throughput","cost per request or routing efficiency"],"story_format_guidance":"Use ARIS: state the architecture problem, your platform design, the implementation choices, and measurable production outcomes. Make the reusable-system boundary explicit, not just a single feature shipped.","citation":"Platform design 24/25 (96%); valued evidence types architecture 20 and delivery 18 deep-analysis samples; agents_orchestration 12/25 (48%)."},{"rank":2,"archetype":"Took an agent or RAG system from POC to reliable production","what_it_proves":"Shows you can move beyond demos into grounded, observable, production-safe AI systems.","pain_points_addressed":["need to choose appropriate solutions through pocs","need to build and scale advanced ai systems in production","need to modernize and improve code quality while integrating ai services"],"metrics_to_include":["evaluation pass rate","hallucination or error reduction","retrieval quality or answer accuracy","workflow completion rate","user adoption","deployment frequency"],"story_format_guidance":"Use STAR: frame the weak prototype or business need, show the architecture and evaluation changes you led, then quantify production quality and adoption. Name guardrails and validation steps if they were part of the delivery.","citation":"AI stack signals: agents_orchestration 12/25 (48%), RAG 9/25 (36%), evaluation_quality 5/25 (20%), vector_search 5/25 (20%); success metrics include handling hallucinations (1) and structured output validation (1)."},{"rank":3,"archetype":"Modernized or integrated complex enterprise systems around AI or cloud services","what_it_proves":"Shows enterprise-readiness, integration judgment, and ability to deliver in non-greenfield environments.","pain_points_addressed":["complex system integration as oracle cloud subscription data travels to multiple systems","need to modernize and improve code quality while integrating ai services","need to troubleshoot application and infrastructure issues in test and prod"],"metrics_to_include":["systems integrated","latency or throughput improvement","defect or incident reduction","migration milestones","developer productivity","release stability"],"story_format_guidance":"Use ARIS: show the pre-existing complexity, the integration or modernization architecture, the rollout path, and the operational results. Emphasize dependency management and production stability.","citation":"Greenfield_split shows both 12 and greenfield 8, implying mixed new-build and existing-system work across 20/25 samples; pain-point examples are single-sample but category-relevant integration and modernization signals."},{"rank":4,"archetype":"Raised reliability, observability, and operational safety of AI/backend systems","what_it_proves":"Shows the production judgment this category values more than generic prompt or tool familiarity.","pain_points_addressed":["need to troubleshoot application and infrastructure issues in test and prod","need to establish ml engineering standards, security, and governance"],"metrics_to_include":["availability or uptime","MTTR","incident count","on-call noise reduction","SLO attainment","latency stability"],"story_format_guidance":"Use STAR with a measurable operations problem. Name the instrumentation, failure-handling, or routing changes you made and tie them to incident, performance, or stability outcomes.","citation":"Valued evidence types reliability 18 deep-analysis samples; hard skill observability 6/25 (24%); success metrics include reliability (4), performance (3), security (2), behaves as expected in production (1)."},{"rank":5,"archetype":"Influenced engineering standards and mentored teams while remaining hands-on","what_it_proves":"Shows the player-coach edge that distinguishes this category from purely individual execution roles without implying formal management.","pain_points_addressed":["need to establish ml engineering standards, security, and governance","need to define and drive ai technical strategy"],"metrics_to_include":["teams adopting standards","reduction in defects or review cycles","faster onboarding or delivery","number of engineers mentored","coverage of reusable patterns"],"story_format_guidance":"Use ARIS: show the delivery problem, the standard or enablement mechanism you introduced, your hands-on role in implementation, and the concrete team-level outcome. Keep people-management claims out unless formally documented.","citation":"Role scope player_coach 11/25 (44%); mentoring 12/25 (48%); org_building 9/25 (36%); hiring only 2/25 (8%)."}],"role_weighting_guidance":{"highest_weight_roles":["Staff/Principal IC roles with architecture ownership for production platforms or distributed systems.","Hands-on AI platform, backend platform, or developer tooling roles that shipped real systems.","Player-coach roles with mentoring or standards-setting, but limited formal management scope."],"expand_in_work_history":["Roles where you owned architecture, integration boundaries, greenfield platform work, or modernization.","Roles where you can quantify reliability, scale, delivery speed, evaluation quality, or security outcomes.","Roles with agent orchestration, RAG, vector retrieval, or guardrails only when those systems were shipped and measured."],"compress_in_work_history":["Pure people-management scope without hands-on technical delivery.","Tool-only experimentation, hackathon-style prototypes, or prompt-only work without production outcomes.","Older application work that lacks architecture, distributed systems, platform, or reliability relevance."],"how_to_frame_non_ai_experience":["Translate strong backend, microservices, CQRS, event-sourcing, or distributed systems work into evidence for AI platform architecture and production reliability.","Use prior cloud/platform roles to prove integration judgment, delivery discipline, and observability foundations for AI systems.","If AI work is newer than platform work, weight the AI roles higher but keep the backend foundation visible because no single AI keyword dominates this category."],"citations":["Seniority and scope: senior_ic 25/25 (100%), IC 14/25 (56%), player_coach 11/25 (44%).","Architecture and delivery: platform design 24/25 (96%); valued evidence types architecture 20, delivery 18, reliability 18, scale 15 deep-analysis samples.","Candidate-mapping themes explicitly connect microservices, RabbitMQ, CQRS, and event-sourcing experience to distributed systems and backend platform design (count 2)."]},"language_and_tone":{"recommended_tone":"architect","formality":"high","preferred_vocabulary":["platform architecture","production AI systems","distributed systems","reliability","observability","agent orchestration","RAG","evaluation","guardrails","cross-functional collaboration"],"avoid_vocabulary":["people manager","hiring leader","AI evangelist","multi-cloud expert","millions-scale","end-to-end owner of everything","research-driven"],"citations":["Architecture dominates: platform design 24/25 (96%); valued evidence types architecture 20, reliability 18, delivery 18 deep-analysis samples.","Soft-skill tone should stay collaborative and technical: collaboration 23/25 (92%), mentoring 12/25 (48%), communication 10/25 (40%).","No hard skill is universal: top hard skill Python is 8/25 (32%), so broad architecture and delivery vocabulary is safer than stack-heavy branding."]},"unsafe_or_weak_framing":{"avoid_claims":["Deep production backend delivery in Go unless the CV clearly proves Go depth.","Ownership of SLOs, incident response, or reliability programs unless the CV shows direct operational scope.","Direct MCP, OpenAI, or Anthropic platform experience if not documented.","Formal people management, hiring authority, or performance management unless explicitly held.","Company-wide AI developer tooling ownership at large scale without adoption metrics.","Full multi-cloud implementation across Bedrock and Vertex AI if the work was only on one cloud or one provider.","HIPAA, PHI, or healthcare compliance ownership without direct delivery evidence in that environment."],"buzzword_patterns":["Tool-brand lists without shipped system outcomes.","Agentic AI language without architecture, evaluation, or reliability proof.","RAG language that implies durable memory or self-correcting systems when the work was only partial retrieval or workflow support.","Typescript-first or developer-tools-platform claims when the work was primarily Python or backend infrastructure."],"title_inflation_risks":["Inflating Staff/Principal IC work into Director, Head, or VP language.","Using AI Engineering Manager titles when the real evidence is mentoring or player-coach influence only.","Claiming principal-wide org ownership when evidence is limited to a platform or program slice."],"research_framing_risks":["Do not add publication, research, or PhD-style framing as a positive asset for this category.","Do not reposition delivery work as model research; the market evidence shows research_heavy_pct 0/25 (0%) and requires_phd_pct 0/25 (0%)."],"domain_or_region_risks":["Do not overfit to fintech, healthcare, or enterprise SaaS unless repeated on the candidate CV; each appears only 2 times in market context.","Do not imply native-language or region-specific requirements; native_language_requirements is empty and collaboration model is mostly remote-first.","Do not overclaim consultancy or budget ownership; consultancy appears once and budget_pnl is 0/25 (0%)."],"citations":["Unsafe claims come directly from deep_analysis unsafe_claims_top, including Go depth (count 2), SLO/incident ownership (count 2), direct MCP/OpenAI/Anthropic experience (count 2), and formal people management or hiring authority (count 2).","Management evidence is limited: hiring 2/25 (8%), performance_management 1/25 (4%), budget_pnl 0/25 (0%).","Research disqualifiers: research_heavy_pct 0/25 (0%), requires_phd_pct 0/25 (0%); native_language_requirements is empty."]},"evidence_ledger":[{"recommendation":"Lead the CV as a Staff/Principal architecture-focused senior IC, not as a manager.","support":["Title families cluster around principal_engineer 13/25 (52%) and staff_engineer 11/25 (44%).","Seniority is senior_ic 25/25 (100%).","Hiring is only 2/25 (8%) and performance management 1/25 (4%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Make platform architecture, production delivery, and reliability the spine of the profile.","support":["Platform design appears in 24/25 roles (96%).","Deep-analysis valued evidence types: architecture 20, reliability 18, delivery 18.","Success metrics cluster around reliability (4), performance (3), and scalability (2)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Treat agent orchestration, RAG, evaluation, and guardrails as strong differentiators only when they are truly evidenced.","support":["Agents_orchestration appears in 12/25 (48%).","RAG appears in 9/25 (36%), vector_search in 5/25 (20%), evaluation_quality in 5/25 (20%), and guardrails_governance in 7/25 (28%).","Framework evidence is fragmented, with LangChain highest at only 5/25 (20%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Do not over-optimize the CV around one technical keyword; there is no single universal technical keyword in this category.","support":["Top hard skill is Python at 8/25 (32%).","Distributed systems is 7/25 (28%) and observability 6/25 (24%).","Cloud and language signals are spread across AWS 4/25 (16%), Go 4/25 (16%), Java 4/25 (16%), TypeScript 3/25 (12%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Show collaboration and mentoring as proof of scope, but keep formal leadership claims narrow.","support":["Collaboration appears in 23/25 roles (92%).","Mentoring appears in 12/25 (48%) and player_coach scope in 11/25 (44%).","Org_building appears in 9/25 (36%), but hiring is only 2/25 (8%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Keep research/publication/PhD language out of positive positioning for this category.","support":["Requires_phd_pct is 0/25 (0%).","Research_heavy_pct is 0/25 (0%).","The category evidence is applied and delivery-oriented: architecture 20, reliability 18, delivery 18 deep-analysis samples."],"confidence":"high"}   	,
./data/eval/raw/head_of_ai_global/jd_texts/59_everai_senior_devops_engineer_full_remote_slovenia.md:10:Our Vision & Products🚀 EverAI — Building the Future of AI CompanionshipOne of the Top 15 Largest & Fastest-Growing AI Companies in the World35+ Million Users in 2 years — Help Us Reach 100M first, 500M nextAt EverAI, we’re shaping what it means to connect with AI. With 35+ millionusers and counting, we're not just building products — we're creating entirelynew categories.Our flagship product is the world’s largest AI girlfriend/boyfriend platform,redefining relationships for millions. It is governed by our proprietarymoderation system, EverGuard — an internal AI designed to ensure everything webuild is safe, ethical, and human-first.And we’re only just getting started!Our TeamWe are an enthusiastic, passionate and hardworking team of 70 people. Ourfounding team has strong entrepreneurial experience building and scaling webproducts from 0 to IPO.Alexis Soulopoulos [CEO] * 10+ years in Tech Executive Leadership * Co-Founder Mad Paws Holdings (from 0 to IPO) * Forbes 30 under 30 + Deloitte TechFast50 ’22 & ‘23 Michael Monin [Co-founder & CTO] * 10+ years as CTO / COO (web2/web3), 1+ year in AI/LLM * Serial-entrepreneur: MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue) and Zipchat (AI Chatbot for E-commerce brands) Thomas Lacroix [Co-founder & CMO] * 8+ years in Customer Acquisition & E-commerce Growth * Serial-entrepreneur: Curatible (sold to Blackstone) and MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue) Maruša Fasano [CFO/Legal] * 25+ years in Finance, Strategy, M&A * Ex-CFO/M&A @Curatible (exited to Blackstone) * Ex-President of the Board @SotremoSA (exited) * Co-founder/CFO @SoftOne (exited) Your RoleOur user base and tech team are expanding rapidly, we are therefore hiring aSenior DevOps Engineer to help us build and scale our platform and support ourengineering teams. You’ll have the opportunity to help define our roadmap andfind the best technical solutions to help our customers. You will also have timeto run some experiments and bring new ideas to the table.Reporting directly to our DevOps Lead, Mate, you will be responsible for: * Interacting with the engineers to provide infrastructure support * Manage, monitor and scale our existing services * Provision infrastructure and platform services through Infrastructure-as-Code, code reviews and testing You will be working with Michael (Co-founder & CTO), along with the Product teamand the Engineering team (web developers, SRE, data scientists).Your QualificationsMust-haves💼 5+ years of experience: * Public cloud, Kubernetes, GitOps * Observability through logs, metrics and tracing * Infrastucture-as-Code, Terraform, Helm * Ability to read and understand application code (Go, Python, shell) * In tech startups or any similarly agile and fast-paced environment 🗣 Strong communication & collaborative skills (perfectly fluent in English)🎯 Goal-oriented, ownership and commitment⚡️ Doer mindset - we are moving fast and need people who can balance execution,planning, and strategy🧢 Humble - willing to learn, open to feedback🫶🏻 User-centricity - you are proud of what you build and you share ourobsession for amazing user experience🍭 #NSFW - you are comfortable building products that are based on uncensoredmodels and contentBonus points * Past experience and/or interest in data science and generative AI (NLP, ML, MLOps, etc.) * Location: you must be able to work within ±4 CET Why EverAI?📈 Exponential Growth: From 35M+ users in 2 years, to 100M next — and 500Mbeyond🚀 Track Record of Category-Creating Innovation: We consistently launchworld-first AI applications — setting the pace, not following it🌍 Global Impact: Top-tier user growth, real-world adoption, and culturalrelevance🧠 Proven Leadership: A senior team that’s launched, scaled, and exited & IPO’dmultiple scale ups — now fully focused on reshaping AI companionship👥 Elite Remote Team: 100% remote and built to win — world-class talent fromTier 1 tech companies, with a culture of ownership, velocity, and radicalcreativity🛡️ Ethical Core: Our AI ecosystem is governed by EverGuard, our proprietary AImoderation technology, ensuring responsible development at scaleWhat we offer✍️ Contract Type: We prefer B2B, but we’re flexible, what matters is long-termcommitment and impact📍 Work From Anywhere: Fully remote. Choose the environment where you do yourbest work🏝️ Paid Time Off: 4 weeks (20 working days) of PTO per year to recharge andreset👨👩👧👦 Annual Gathering: A yearly in-person meetup to connect, brainstorm,and celebrate wins together❤️🩹 Health & Wellness Support: Up to $200 per year for wellbeing expenses +unlimited 1:1 sessions with psychologists and lifestyle experts through OpenUp(also available for up to three family members)🏢 Co-Working Space Budget: Work from a co-working space up to twice per month(35 EUR / 40 USD per visit) to stay inspired and connected📚 Learning Budget: Dedicated funds to support your professional growth:courses, books, conferences, events, or certifications💻 Equipment: Company laptop provided + monitor budget up to $250 for yourworkspace setup⚡ AI Tools Access: Premium access to ChatGPT, Cursor, Hugging Face, and others,to power your ideas and workflows🎯 Top Tier Talent Is Our MultiplierWe’re a fully remote group of A-players from Tier 1 tech, led by an exec teamwho’ve launched, scaled, and exited multiple companies. We move fast, and caredeeply about what we build — and who we build it with.We’re looking for exceptional talent ready to ship & distribute world-first AIproducts at scale, fast, and co-create with us this category-defining business.If that’s you — reach out and apply!💡 External Referral ProgramKnow someone who could be a great fit for this role? You can refer them throughthe EverAI External Referral Program and earn a bonus of up to $2,500 if they’rehired. Submit a referral here.Show more Show less
./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_global/jd_texts/44_version_1_solution_architect_cloud_ai_automation.md:10:Company DescriptionVersion 1 has celebrated over 28 years in Technology Services and continues tobe trusted by global brands to deliver solutions that drive customer success.Our expertise enables our customers to navigate the rapidly changingDigital-First world we live in. We foster strong partnerships with leadingtechnology giants including Microsoft, AWS, Oracle, Red Hat, OutSystems,Snowflake, ensuring that our customers are provided with the highest qualitysolutions and services.We’re An Award-winning Employer Reflecting How Our Employees Are At The VeryHeart Of Version 1 And What We Do * UK & Ireland's premier AWS, Microsoft & Oracle partner * 3300+ strong, €350/£300m revenue business * 10+ years as a Great Place to Work in Ireland & UK * Best Workplace for Women in the UK & Ireland by GPTW * Best Workplace for Wellbeing in the UK by GPTW We’re a core values driven company, we hire people who share our values, and wereward those who display and foster them, it’s deeply embedded within our DNA.Invest in us and we’ll invest in you!Job Description * Architect scalable, secure, and cost-effective cloud and AI solutions aligned with business goals. * Lead the design and implementation of cloud-native architectures using Azure and/or AWS. * Define and implement multi-cloud and hybrid cloud strategies. * Evaluate emerging technologies and recommend best-fit solutions. * Guide cross-functional teams including developers, data scientists, and business analysts. * Integrate AI/ML capabilities into enterprise solutions using services like Azure Cognitive Services and AWS SageMaker. * Design and implement microservices, API management, and event-driven architectures. * Automate infrastructure using Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tools such as Terraform and Bicep. * Oversee DevOps practices including CI/CD pipelines and security best practices. * Support the development of data lakes, data warehouses, and ETL pipelines. * Provide architectural governance and ensure alignment with IT strategy and regulatory standards. * Collaborate with stakeholders to define technical architecture and future ICT platforms. * Maintain high-quality architecture documentation and ensure compliance with governance processes. Qualifications * 10+ years experience in ICT Infrastructure, operations and cloud, solution and technical architecture. * Proven experience in cloud architecture (Azure and/or AWS), including governance and security. * Strong understanding of multi-cloud, hybrid cloud, and cloud-native services (serverless, containers, Kubernetes). * Experience with AI/ML integration and lifecycle management (data prep, training, deployment, monitoring). * Deep knowledge of DevOps, CI/CD pipelines, and IaC tools (Terraform, Bicep). * Expertise in application, integration, infrastructure, and security architecture. * Experience designing large-scale on-premise and hybrid cloud business applications. * Familiarity with architecture tools, frameworks, and methodologies. * Strong understanding of non-functional requirements (performance, scalability, availability). * Knowledge of Microsoft Azure services (Application Insights, Redis Cache, Service Bus, etc.). * Understanding of IT governance, regulatory requirements (e.g., GDPR, ISO), and architectural governance. * Experience with API design, microservices, and federated identity providers. * Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to engage stakeholders and document solutions effectively. * Demonstrated ability to shape strategic ICT and digital service direction. Additional InformationWhy Version 1?At Version 1, we believe in providing our employees with a comprehensivebenefits package that prioritises their wellbeing, professional growth, andfinancial stability. * Share in our success with our Quarterly Performance-Related Profit Share Scheme, where employees collectively benefit from a share of our company's profits. * Strong Career Progression & mentorship coaching through our Strength in Balance & Leadership schemes with a dedicated quarterly Pathways Career Development programme. * Flexible/remote working, Version 1 is tremendously understanding of life events and people’s individual circumstances and offer flexibility to help achieve a healthy work life balance. * Financial Wellbeing initiatives including; Pension, Private Healthcare Cover, Life Assurance, Financial advice and an Employee Discount scheme. * Employee Wellbeing schemes including Gym Discounts, Bike to Work, Fitness classes, Mindfulness Workshops, Employee Assistance Programme and much more. Generous holiday allowance, enhanced maternity/paternity leave, marriage/civil partnership leave and special leave policies. * Educational assistance, incentivised certifications, and accreditations, including AWS, Microsoft, Oracle, and Red Hat. * Reward schemes including Version 1’s Annual Excellence Awards & ‘Call-Out’ platform. * Environment, Social and Community First initiatives allow you to get involved in local fundraising and development opportunities as part of fostering our diversity, inclusion and belonging schemes. And many more exciting benefits… drop us a note to find out more.Ekta Bahl - Talent Acquisition Capability PartnerShow more Show less
