./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_eea/jd_texts/15_globallogic_ai_computer_vision_solution_architect_irc281985.md:10:DescriptionJoin GlobalLogic’s Architects Team within the Healthcare Business Unit,supporting clients across the EMEA region. This strategic role focuses onengaging new clients, designing advanced AI solutions for medical imageanalysis, and launching projects involving computer vision, deep learning, andgenerative AI. You’ll work on cutting-edge use cases like diagnostic assistance,surgical planning, and radiology automation, bringing meaningful impact topatient care. If you’re passionate about AI in healthcare and want to driveinnovation with real-world results, we’d love to hear from you.Requirements * Master’s or PhD in Computer Science, AI, Biomedical Engineering, or a related field. * 7+ years of experience in AI/ML with at least 4 years focused on computer vision and deep learning. * Proven experience with CNN architectures (e.g., ResNet, UNet, EfficientNet, VGG). * Experience with GANs (e.g., CycleGAN, StyleGAN, Pix2Pix) and synthetic image generation. * Hands-on with TensorFlow, PyTorch, OpenCV, and related vision libraries. * Strong understanding of preprocessing techniques for medical imaging data (e.g., DICOM, NIfTI). * Familiarity with training in cloud environments (Azure, AWS, GCP). * Experience in deploying models and integrating with PACS systems or cloud-native imaging stacks. * Solid understanding of model performance metrics and validation strategies for imaging. * Excellent communication skills and at least Upper-Intermediate English level. Preferred Qualifications (Nice To Have) * Experience with FDA/CE Class B or C medical imaging products. * Familiarity with explainable AI (Grad-CAM, LIME) and fairness techniques for imaging models. * Knowledge of FHIR, HL7, and healthcare data standards. * Understanding of HIPAA, GDPR, or other relevant data protection regulations. * Experience with AI for surgical robotics, augmented reality in healthcare, or histopathology image analysis. * Involvement in technical presales or client advisory initiatives. Job responsibilities * Design, develop, and optimize AI models for computer vision, segmentation, objects detection, image classification, etc. * Lead computer vision and AI solutioning in client engagements and presales discussions. * Build CNN- and GAN-based architectures tailored for healthcare and medical imaging use cases. * Prepare and preprocess large-scale datasets from modalities like X-ray, CT, MRI, and digital pathology. * Guide annotation strategies and quality control for labeled data. * Collaborate with cloud, DevOps, and QA teams to integrate models into production pipelines. * Ensure model robustness, explainability, and regulatory readiness (e.g., traceability, reproducibility). * Conduct technical workshops and communicate complex concepts to clients in an accessible way. * Stay current with research trends and evaluate new techniques for potential integration. * Contribute to internal accelerators, frameworks, and IP development. What we offerCulture of caring. At GlobalLogic, we prioritize a culture of caring. Acrossevery region and department, at every level, we consistently put people first.From day one, you’ll experience an inclusive culture of acceptance andbelonging, where you’ll have the chance to build meaningful connections withcollaborative teammates, supportive managers, and compassionate leaders.Learning and development. We are committed to your continuous learning anddevelopment. You’ll learn and grow daily in an environment with manyopportunities to try new things, sharpen your skills, and advance your career atGlobalLogic. With our Career Navigator tool as just one example, GlobalLogicoffers a rich array of programs, training curricula, and hands-on opportunitiesto grow personally and professionally.Interesting & meaningful work. GlobalLogic is known for engineering impact forand with clients around the world. As part of our team, you’ll have the chanceto work on projects that matter. Each is a unique opportunity to engage yourcuriosity and creative problem-solving skills as you help clients reimaginewhat’s possible and bring new solutions to market. In the process, you’ll havethe privilege of working on some of the most cutting-edge and impactfulsolutions shaping the world today.Balance and flexibility. We believe in the importance of balance andflexibility. With many functional career areas, roles, and work arrangements,you can explore ways of achieving the perfect balance between your work andlife. Your life extends beyond the office, and we always do our best to help youintegrate and balance the best of work and life, having fun along the way!High-trust organization. We are a high-trust organization where integrity iskey. By joining GlobalLogic, you’re placing your trust in a safe, reliable, andethical global company. Integrity and trust are a cornerstone of our valueproposition to our employees and clients. You will find truthfulness, candor,and integrity in everything we do.About GlobalLogicGlobalLogic, a Hitachi Group Company, is a trusted digital engineering partnerto the world’s largest and most forward-thinking companies. Since 2000, we’vebeen at the forefront of the digital revolution – helping create some of themost innovative and widely used digital products and experiences. Today wecontinue to collaborate with clients in transforming businesses and redefiningindustries through intelligent products, platforms, and services.Show more Show less
./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_ksa_uae/jd_texts/24_capgemini_engineering_senior_solution_architect_ai_cloud_platform.md:10:At Capgemini Engineering, the world leader in engineering services, we bringtogether a global team of visionary engineers, scientists, and architects tohelp the world’s most innovative companies unleash their full potential. Fromautonomous cars to life-saving robots, our digital and software technologyexperts think outside the box as they provide unique R&D and engineeringservices across all industries. Join us for a career full of opportunities.Where you can make a difference.Where no two days are the same.Your RoleWe are seeking a Senior Solution Architect – AI & Cloud Platforms (Generative &Agentic AI) to define, govern, and ensure the successful delivery ofenterprise‑scale digital and AI platforms in regulated and governmentenvironments. You will translate business and product requirements into secure,scalable, and compliant architectures, with a primary emphasis on GenAI andmulti‑agent systems - including sovereign/private LLM deployments, RAG patterns,agentic orchestration, and LLMOps - while ensuring robust platform foundationsacross on‑prem, private cloud, and hybrid environments. You will collaboratewith engineering, AI, DevOps, security, and product teams to drive architecturefrom strategy to production.Key ResponsibilitiesStrategic & Client Leadership * Shape enterprise AI & platform strategy and convert functional/non‑functional requirements into GenAI‑first solution architectures (RAG, tool‑use, function‑calling, multi‑agent orchestration) with clear trade‑offs and compliance alignment. * Present architectures and key decisions to senior stakeholders (including government entities); provide documentation and rationale to support design reviews and approvals. * Govern architectural consistency across programs and promote reuse of shared platform services.Technical Leadership & Architecture * Define end‑to‑end solution architectures (HLD/LLD, data‑/control‑flow, interface specs) across dev, staging, and production; ensure alignment across multiple applications and platforms. * Design and oversee enterprise‑grade GenAI solutions, including private/sovereign LLM deployments, RAG, model orchestration, and AI workflows with data classification, privacy, and governance baked in. * Architect agentic AI solutions and multi‑agent systems, specifying patterns for agent planning, memory, tool‑use, and inter‑agent collaboration using LangChain, LangGraph, LlamaIndex, and workflow tools like n8n and Model Context Protocol (MCP). * Define Kubernetes‑based platform patterns (isolation, multi‑tenancy, network ingress/egress) and hybrid deployment topologies (on‑prem/private cloud). * Establish security controls for AI and platforms (authn/authz, token management aligned to enterprise identity standards; data protection; prompt handling; output safeguards) and lead inputs to threat modeling and VAPT.Delivery Leadership * Provide ongoing architectural governance through development, testing, and release; review designs/implementations to ensure fidelity to the approved architecture. * Partner with DevOps to define CI/CD pipelines, environment promotion strategies, observability/monitoring/logging, and operational readiness (scalability, resilience, and continuity). * Support incident response and decision‑making during delivery to minimize operational risk and ensure SLO/SLI alignment.People & Capability Building * Act as the primary technical liaison across engineering, AI, DevOps, security, and product; mentor teams on architectural standards, documentation rigor, and secure‑by‑design practices. * Codify and share reference architectures, patterns, and guardrails for GenAI, agentic AI, and platform services for reuse across programs. * Profile * Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field (or equivalent experience). * 8–15+ years in solution/system/platform architecture with a track record delivering large‑scale enterprise or government platforms in regulated contexts. * Proven breadth across application architecture, infrastructure, security, and AI platforms, including GenAI and model integration patterns. * Deep experience with Kubernetes‑based platforms (on‑prem/private cloud), CI/CD and infrastructure‑as‑code, and secure API‑ and service‑oriented design. * Demonstrated ability to lead security, compliance, and assurance activities (authn/authz and token patterns aligned with enterprise identity, threat modeling, and VAPT leadership). * Excellent stakeholder communication, documentation, problem‑solving, and the ability to operate in complex, multi‑party environments.Preferred Skills * Experience in government/public sector or highly regulated industries; exposure to sovereign cloud, private AI platforms, or air‑gapped environments. * Prior hands‑on experience in software engineering or DevOps roles, enabling pragmatic, implementation‑aware architectural decisions. * Practical familiarity with agentic AI frameworks (LangChain, LangGraph, LlamaIndex), workflow tooling (n8n, MCP), and LLMOps evaluation/guardrail patterns at enterprise scale.What You’ll Love About Working Here * We recognize the significance of flexible work arrangements to provide support. Be it remote work, or flexible work hours, you will get an environment to maintain a healthy work-life balance. * At the heart of our mission is your career growth. Our array of career growth programs and diverse professions are crafted to support you in exploring a world of opportunities. * Equip yourself with valuable certifications in the latest technologies.About CapgeminiCapgemini is a global leader in partnering with companies to transform andmanage their business by harnessing the power of technology. The Group is guidedeveryday by its purpose of unleashing human energy through technology for aninclusive and sustainable future. It is a responsible and diverse organizationof over 360,000 team members in more than 50 countries. With its strong 55-yearheritage and deep industry expertise, Capgemini is trusted by its clients toaddress the entire breadth of their business needs, from strategy and design tooperations, fuelled by the fast evolving and innovative world of cloud, data,AI, connectivity, software, digital engineering and platforms. The Groupreported in 2022 global revenues of €22 billion.Show more Show less
