./data/eval/raw/head_of_ai_global/jd_texts/36_everai_senior_ruby_on_rails_engineer_full_remote_spain.md:10:Our Vision & Products🚀 EverAI — Building the Future of AI CompanionshipOne of the Top 15 Largest & Fastest-Growing AI Companies in the World35+ Million Users in 2 years — Help Us Reach 100M first, 500M nextAt EverAI, we’re shaping what it means to connect with AI. With 35+ millionusers and counting, we're not just building products — we're creating entirelynew categories.Our flagship product is the world’s largest AI girlfriend/boyfriend platform,redefining relationships for millions. It is governed by our proprietarymoderation system, EverGuard — an internal AI designed to ensure everything webuild is safe, ethical, and human-first.And we’re only just getting started!Our TeamWe are an enthusiastic, passionate and hardworking team of 70 people. Ourfounding team has strong entrepreneurial experience building and scaling webproducts from 0 to IPO.Alexis Soulopoulos [CEO] * 10+ years in Tech Executive Leadership * Co-Founder Mad Paws Holdings (from 0 to IPO) * Forbes 30 under 30 + Deloitte TechFast50 ’22 & ‘23 Michael Monin [Co-founder & CTO] * 10+ years as CTO / COO (web2/web3), 1+ year in AI/LLM * Serial-entrepreneur: MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue) and Zipchat (AI Chatbot for E-commerce brands) Thomas Lacroix [Co-founder & CMO] * 8+ years in Customer Acquisition & E-commerce Growth * Serial-entrepreneur: Curatible (sold to Blackstone) and MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue) Maruša Fasano [CFO/Legal] * 25+ years in Finance, Strategy, M&A * Ex-CFO/M&A @Curatible (exited to Blackstone) * Ex-President of the Board @SotremoSA (exited) * Co-founder/CFO @SoftOne (exited) Your RoleOur tech team is expanding rapidly to keep pace with the ambitious featureroadmap we've set out. We are therefore hiring experienced Senior SoftwareEngineers (Back-end / Ruby) to help us build and scale our product. You’ll havethe opportunity to help define our roadmap and find the best technical solutionsto help our customers. You will also have time to run some experiments and bringnew ideas to the table.Reporting directly to our Tech Lead, you will be responsible for: * Interacting with the Product Manager to review project specs * Preparing integration plans, break-downs, and estimations * Hands-on code implementation, PRs, code reviews, testing, etc. You'll be working with Michael (co-founder and CTO) along with the product teamand the engineering team (web developers, SRE, data scientists).💎 NB: while we remain open to full-stack expertise, we are looking for peoplewith a strong edge on back-end development using Ruby-on-Rails.Your QualificationsMust-haves💼 5+ years of experience: * As a back-end or full-stack software engineer - recent experience with Ruby-on-Rails is mandatory * In tech scale-ups or any similarly agile and fast-paced environment * On large-scale products where your code was used by thousands of monthly users 🗣 Strong communication & collaborative skills (perfectly fluent in English)🧢 Ownership and commitment - we’re looking for owners, not renters⚡️ Doer mindset - we are moving fast and we need people who can find the rightbalance between software craftsmanship and velocity🫶🏻 User-centricity - you are proud of what you build and you share ourobsession for amazing user experience🍭 #NSFW - you are comfortable building products that are based on uncensoredmodels and contentBonus points * Past experience and/or interest in data science and generative AI (NLP, ML, MLOps…) * Experience working with globally distributed teams Why EverAI?📈 Exponential Growth: From 35M+ users in 2 years, to 100M next — and 500Mbeyond🚀 Track Record of Category-Creating Innovation: We consistently launchworld-first AI applications — setting the pace, not following it🌍 Global Impact: Top-tier user growth, real-world adoption, and culturalrelevance🧠 Proven Leadership: A senior team that’s launched, scaled, and exited & IPO’dmultiple scale ups — now fully focused on reshaping AI companionship👥 Elite Remote Team: 100% remote and built to win — world-class talent fromTier 1 tech companies, with a culture of ownership, velocity, and radicalcreativity🛡️ Ethical Core: Our AI ecosystem is governed by EverGuard, our proprietary AImoderation technology, ensuring responsible development at scaleWhat we offer✍️ Contract Type: We prefer B2B, but we’re flexible, what matters is long-termcommitment and impact📍 Work From Anywhere: Fully remote. Choose the environment where you do yourbest work🏝️ Paid Time Off: 4 weeks (20 working days) of PTO per year to recharge andreset👨👩👧👦 Annual Gathering: A yearly in-person meetup to connect, brainstorm,and celebrate wins together❤️🩹 Health & Wellness Support: Up to $200 per year for wellbeing expenses +unlimited 1:1 sessions with psychologists and lifestyle experts through OpenUp(also available for up to three family members)🏢 Co-Working Space Budget: Work from a co-working space up to twice per month(35 EUR / 40 USD per visit) to stay inspired and connected📚 Learning Budget: Dedicated funds to support your professional growth:courses, books, conferences, events, or certifications💻 Equipment: Company laptop provided + monitor budget up to $250 for yourworkspace setup⚡ AI Tools Access: Premium access to ChatGPT, Cursor, Hugging Face, and others,to power your ideas and workflows🎯 Top Tier Talent Is Our MultiplierWe’re a fully remote group of A-players from Tier 1 tech, led by an exec teamwho’ve launched, scaled, and exited multiple companies. We move fast, and caredeeply about what we build — and who we build it with.We’re looking for exceptional talent ready to ship & distribute world-first AIproducts at scale, fast, and co-create with us this category-defining business.If that’s you — reach out and apply!💡 External Referral ProgramKnow someone who could be a great fit for this role? You can refer them throughthe EverAI External Referral Program and earn a bonus of up to $2,500 if they’rehired. Submit a referral here.Show more Show less
./data/eval/raw/head_of_ai_global/jd_texts/64_everai_senior_devops_engineer_full_remote_lithuania.md:10:Our Vision & Products🚀 EverAI — Building the Future of AI CompanionshipOne of the Top 15 Largest & Fastest-Growing AI Companies in the World35+ Million Users in 2 years — Help Us Reach 100M first, 500M nextAt EverAI, we’re shaping what it means to connect with AI. With 35+ millionusers and counting, we're not just building products — we're creating entirelynew categories.Our flagship product is the world’s largest AI girlfriend/boyfriend platform,redefining relationships for millions. It is governed by our proprietarymoderation system, EverGuard — an internal AI designed to ensure everything webuild is safe, ethical, and human-first.And we’re only just getting started!Our TeamWe are an enthusiastic, passionate and hardworking team of 70 people. Ourfounding team has strong entrepreneurial experience building and scaling webproducts from 0 to IPO.Alexis Soulopoulos [CEO] * 10+ years in Tech Executive Leadership * Co-Founder Mad Paws Holdings (from 0 to IPO) * Forbes 30 under 30 + Deloitte TechFast50 ’22 & ‘23 Michael Monin [Co-founder & CTO] * 10+ years as CTO / COO (web2/web3), 1+ year in AI/LLM * Serial-entrepreneur: MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue) and Zipchat (AI Chatbot for E-commerce brands) Thomas Lacroix [Co-founder & CMO] * 8+ years in Customer Acquisition & E-commerce Growth * Serial-entrepreneur: Curatible (sold to Blackstone) and MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue) Maruša Fasano [CFO/Legal] * 25+ years in Finance, Strategy, M&A * Ex-CFO/M&A @Curatible (exited to Blackstone) * Ex-President of the Board @SotremoSA (exited) * Co-founder/CFO @SoftOne (exited) Your RoleOur user base and tech team are expanding rapidly, we are therefore hiring aSenior DevOps Engineer to help us build and scale our platform and support ourengineering teams. You’ll have the opportunity to help define our roadmap andfind the best technical solutions to help our customers. You will also have timeto run some experiments and bring new ideas to the table.Reporting directly to our DevOps Lead, Mate, you will be responsible for: * Interacting with the engineers to provide infrastructure support * Manage, monitor and scale our existing services * Provision infrastructure and platform services through Infrastructure-as-Code, code reviews and testing You will be working with Michael (Co-founder & CTO), along with the Product teamand the Engineering team (web developers, SRE, data scientists).Your QualificationsMust-haves💼 5+ years of experience: * Public cloud, Kubernetes, GitOps * Observability through logs, metrics and tracing * Infrastucture-as-Code, Terraform, Helm * Ability to read and understand application code (Go, Python, shell) * In tech startups or any similarly agile and fast-paced environment 🗣 Strong communication & collaborative skills (perfectly fluent in English)🎯 Goal-oriented, ownership and commitment⚡️ Doer mindset - we are moving fast and need people who can balance execution,planning, and strategy🧢 Humble - willing to learn, open to feedback🫶🏻 User-centricity - you are proud of what you build and you share ourobsession for amazing user experience🍭 #NSFW - you are comfortable building products that are based on uncensoredmodels and contentBonus points * Past experience and/or interest in data science and generative AI (NLP, ML, MLOps, etc.) * Location: you must be able to work within ±4 CET Why EverAI?📈 Exponential Growth: From 35M+ users in 2 years, to 100M next — and 500Mbeyond🚀 Track Record of Category-Creating Innovation: We consistently launchworld-first AI applications — setting the pace, not following it🌍 Global Impact: Top-tier user growth, real-world adoption, and culturalrelevance🧠 Proven Leadership: A senior team that’s launched, scaled, and exited & IPO’dmultiple scale ups — now fully focused on reshaping AI companionship👥 Elite Remote Team: 100% remote and built to win — world-class talent fromTier 1 tech companies, with a culture of ownership, velocity, and radicalcreativity🛡️ Ethical Core: Our AI ecosystem is governed by EverGuard, our proprietary AImoderation technology, ensuring responsible development at scaleWhat We Offer✍️ Contract Type: We prefer B2B, but we’re flexible, what matters is long-termcommitment and impact📍 Work From Anywhere: Fully remote. Choose the environment where you do yourbest work🏝️ Paid Time Off: 4 weeks (20 working days) of PTO per year to recharge andreset👨👩👧👦 Annual Gathering: A yearly in-person meetup to connect, brainstorm,and celebrate wins together❤️🩹 Health & Wellness Support: Up to $200 per year for wellbeing expenses +unlimited 1:1 sessions with psychologists and lifestyle experts through OpenUp(also available for up to three family members)🏢 Co-Working Space Budget: Work from a co-working space up to twice per month(35 EUR / 40 USD per visit) to stay inspired and connected📚 Learning Budget: Dedicated funds to support your professional growth:courses, books, conferences, events, or certifications💻 Equipment: Company laptop provided + monitor budget up to $250 for yourworkspace setup⚡ AI Tools Access: Premium access to ChatGPT, Cursor, Hugging Face, and others,to power your ideas and workflows🎯 Top Tier Talent Is Our MultiplierWe’re a fully remote group of A-players from Tier 1 tech, led by an exec teamwho’ve launched, scaled, and exited multiple companies. We move fast, and caredeeply about what we build — and who we build it with.We’re looking for exceptional talent ready to ship & distribute world-first AIproducts at scale, fast, and co-create with us this category-defining business.If that’s you — reach out and apply!💡 External Referral ProgramKnow someone who could be a great fit for this role? You can refer them throughthe EverAI External Referral Program and earn a bonus of up to $2,500 if they’rehired. Submit a referral here.Show more Show less
./data/eval/blueprints/debug/ai_architect_global/20260415_165238/attempt_01_lightweight_repair_raw_output.txt:1:{"meta":{"category_id":"ai_architect_global","category_name":"AI Architect — Global/Remote","macro_family":"ai_architect","priority":"primary_target","confidence":"high","total_jobs":88,"deep_analysis_count":20,"low_sample_mode":false,"noisy_title_mode":false,"uncertainty_note":"Sample is strong enough for specific guidance, but no single hard technical keyword clears 60%, so do not overfit the CV around one tool or cloud badge alone."},"category_signature":{"one_sentence_summary":"A top-third CV for this category should present a senior hands-on architect who designs and ships production AI platforms and enterprise integrations, translates architecture into delivery, and proves governance, scale, and cross-functional execution without inflating people-management scope.","distinctive_signals":["Architecture-first category: platform design appears in 87/88 roles (98.9%), with greenfield plus optimization work more common than pure greenfield (both 42% vs greenfield 7% vs optimization 6%).","Role shape is senior IC with some player-coach behavior, not people management: senior_ic 79%, ic 49%, player_coach 38%, manager 1%; hiring and performance management each 2/88 (2.3%).","AI architecture emphasis is production-oriented and enterprise-facing: agents/orchestration 34/88 (38.6%), guardrails/governance 33/88 (37.5%), RAG 25/88 (28.4%), evaluation/quality 18/88 (20.5%), consulting/consultancy signals 20 roles combined."],"citations":["platform_design 87/88 (98.9%)","senior_ic 79%, ic 49%, player_coach 38%, manager 1%","hiring 2/88 (2.3%), performance_management 2/88 (2.3%)","agents_orchestration 34/88 (38.6%), guardrails_governance 33/88 (37.5%), rag 25/88 (28.4%), evaluation_quality 18/88 (20.5%)"]},"headline_pattern":{"recommended_structure":"<Safe architect title family> | Enterprise AI / Solution Architecture | Production GenAI, Agents, Integration, Governance","safe_title_families":["AI Architect","AI Solution Architect","Solutions Architect"],"safe_title_variants":["AI Solution Architect","Generative AI Solution Architect","AI Software Architect","ML/LLM Technical Architect","Senior Solution Architect"],"avoid_title_variants":["Head of AI","VP AI","Director of AI","Chief AI Architect","AI Research Scientist","Engineering Manager"],"evidence_first_rules":["Use a title family supported by actual prior role scope; solutions_architect titles dominate the sample (50%) and ai_architect titles are also common (37%).","Pair the title with 2-4 proven architecture keywords, not a long tool list; no hard skill exceeds 60%, so the headline should not hinge on one framework or cloud.","Only use customer-facing or solution-architecture wording if the CV shows client or stakeholder interaction; stakeholder management appears in 39/88 roles (44.3%), but deep-analysis flags customer-facing claims as unsafe if not evidenced.","Do not imply people leadership in the headline unless explicit; hiring and performance management are each only 2/88 (2.3%)."],"citations":["title_families: solutions_architect 50%, ai_architect 37%","stakeholder_management 39/88 (44.3%)","hiring 2/88 (2.3%), performance_management 2/88 (2.3%)","hard_skills_top: python 29/88 (33.0%) is highest; no hard skill >= 60%"]},"tagline_profile_angle":{"positioning_angle":["Position as a hands-on AI architecture lead for enterprise systems: show platform design, system integration, production rollout, and governance rather than pure model research.","Position as a translator between business/stakeholders and engineering delivery when true: communication 67/88 (76.1%), collaboration 56/88 (63.6%), stakeholder management 39/88 (44.3%)."],"foreground":["Show architecture decisions, delivery outcomes, scale, reliability, evaluation, governance, and cost-aware productionization; these evidence types dominate deep analysis: architecture 20, delivery 19, scale 15, reliability 11, evaluation 11, governance 10, cost 7."],"avoid":["Avoid presenting as a pure people manager, hiring leader, or org builder; org_building is 10/88 (11.4%) and direct management signals are minimal.","Avoid research/publication framing; requires_phd is 0/88 (0.0%) and research_heavy is 0/88 (0.0%).","Avoid generic 'LLM expert' copy without enterprise integration proof, architecture proof, and delivery metrics."],"safe_positioning":["Safe: 'Senior AI architect delivering production RAG/agent systems, enterprise integrations, and guardrailed rollout' when those elements are evidenced.","Safe: 'Hands-on solution architect for AI-enabled platforms across cloud, APIs, and distributed systems' when cloud and integration work are shown.","Safe: 'Player-coach technical lead' only if mentoring, design reviews, or implementation guidance are evidenced; mentoring appears in 18/88 (20.5%), while formal management is weak."],"unsafe_positioning":["Unsafe without evidence: customer-facing solution architecture, full-stack delivery, DevOps/infrastructure ownership, AWS ownership, public-sector specialization, German C1, DSGVO/EU AI Act program ownership.","Unsafe without evidence: executive ownership of strategy, budget, P&L, or org design; budget_pnl is 0/88 (0.0%)."],"citations":["communication 67/88 (76.1%), collaboration 56/88 (63.6%), stakeholder_management 39/88 (44.3%)","valued_evidence_types: architecture 20, delivery 19, scale 15, reliability 11, evaluation 11, governance 10, cost 7","org_building 10/88 (11.4%), hiring 2/88 (2.3%), performance_management 2/88 (2.3%), budget_pnl 0/88 (0.0%)","requires_phd 0/88 (0.0%), research_heavy 0/88 (0.0%)"]},"core_competency_themes":[{"section_name":"Architecture And Integration","themes":[{"theme":"Enterprise AI platform and solution architecture","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This category is architecture-led; show target architectures, system boundaries, platform patterns, and how AI components fit into enterprise stacks. Prove both new design and improvement work, not just prototypes.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keyword. Mention 'AI architecture' or 'solution architecture' 2-3 times across headline, profile, and experience if true. Pair once with 'platform design' and once with 'enterprise architecture' or 'target architecture' if true.","citation":"platform_design 87/88 (98.9%); solution architecture 11/88 (12.5%); valued evidence: architecture 20, delivery 19"},{"theme":"Distributed integration across APIs, microservices, and data flows","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"The market expects architects who connect AI into real systems, especially APIs, microservices, and data pipelines rather than isolated notebooks.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keyword cluster. Mention 1-2 times each for 'APIs', 'microservices', and 'data pipelines' if true. Use niche integration terms once only.","citation":"apis 10/88 (11.4%); microservices 12/88 (13.6%); data pipelines 15/88 (17.0%); pain points include Java/Spring microservice integration (2 mentions)"},{"theme":"Cloud architecture with flexible provider framing","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Cloud is important, but the evidence does not support over-committing to one provider unless explicitly evidenced; multi-cloud appears more often than a single named cloud.","ats_guidance":"Use the actual provider once in headline/profile and 1-2 times in experience only if true. Prefer 'cloud architecture' or 'multi-cloud' over forced AWS/Azure repetition when experience spans both.","citation":"cloud_preference: multi_cloud 29%, Azure 15%, AWS 11%, GCP 1%; aws 14/88 (15.9%); azure 14/88 (15.9%)"}]},{"section_name":"Production GenAI Systems","themes":[{"theme":"Agents and orchestration in production","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Agentic delivery is a distinctive signal here and appears more often than many individual tools. Show orchestration patterns, external system connections, and production controls.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keyword. Mention 'agents' or 'agent orchestration' 2-3 times if true across profile and impact bullets. Name MCP or orchestration frameworks once only if explicitly evidenced.","citation":"agents_orchestration 34/88 (38.6%); pain points include secure scalable AI agents connecting to external systems through MCP (2 mentions)"},{"theme":"RAG, vector search, and knowledge-grounded workflows","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"RAG-style architectures are common enough to materially help positioning, especially when paired with enterprise data integration and retrieval quality.","ats_guidance":"Strong secondary cluster. Mention 'RAG' 1-2 times and 'vector databases' or 'vector search' 1-2 times if true. Name a framework such as LangChain or LlamaIndex once only if true.","citation":"rag 25/88 (28.4%); vector_search 19/88 (21.6%); vector databases 21/88 (23.9%); langchain 20/88 (22.7%)"},{"theme":"Evaluation, quality, and guardrails","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This category values production quality and governance, not just feature shipping. Show evaluation design, risk controls, and measurable quality or safety improvements.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keyword cluster. Mention 'guardrails', 'evaluation', or 'quality' 2-3 times across profile and experience if true; keep vendor observability tools to once only.","citation":"guardrails_governance 33/88 (37.5%); evaluation_quality 18/88 (20.5%); valued evidence: evaluation 11, governance 10, reliability 11"}]},{"section_name":"Delivery And Operationalization","themes":[{"theme":"Production rollout and reliability","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"Deep analysis prioritizes delivery and reliability evidence. CV bullets should show shipped systems, hardening work, and production outcomes rather than design-only influence.","ats_guidance":"Use 'production', 'reliability', or 'rollout' 2-3 times across recent experience if true. Quantify uptime, latency, incident reduction, or release stability where possible.","citation":"valued evidence: delivery 19, reliability 11; success metrics include performance 5, security 3, production-grade delivery 2, reliability 2"},{"theme":"MLOps, CI/CD, Kubernetes, and deployment discipline","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"These are recurring operational signals, but none are universal. They strengthen credibility when the candidate truly owned deployment or lifecycle work.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keyword cluster. Mention each of 'MLOps', 'CI/CD', and 'Kubernetes' 1-2 times if true; do not claim platform ownership if the CV only shows application-layer use.","citation":"mlops 17/88 (19.3%); kubernetes 16/88 (18.2%); ci/cd 11/88 (12.5%); deep-analysis flags DevOps/infrastructure ownership as unsafe if unsupported"},{"theme":"Cost, scalability, and modernization outcomes","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Architect hires are rewarded for making systems tractable at enterprise scale, reducing risk, and modernizing platforms, not just adding AI features.","ats_guidance":"Use quantified outcomes in experience bullets. Mention 'scale', 'performance', 'cost', or 'modernization' 1-2 times where backed by numbers.","citation":"valued evidence: scale 15, cost 7; success metrics include performance 5, scalability 3, technical debt 2, architectural risks 2, modernization opportunities 2"}]},{"section_name":"Stakeholder Translation And Scope Control","themes":[{"theme":"Communication and cross-functional translation","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This category strongly rewards architects who can align technical decisions with delivery stakeholders and adjacent teams.","ats_guidance":"Mention 'communication' or 'cross-functional collaboration' 2-3 times when true, especially in profile and recent roles. Keep it tied to concrete architecture or delivery outcomes.","citation":"communication 67/88 (76.1%); collaboration 56/88 (63.6%)"},{"theme":"Stakeholder management without executive inflation","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Stakeholder translation matters, but the sample does not support broad executive or business-ownership claims by default. Keep scope precise.","ats_guidance":"Mention 'stakeholder management' 1-2 times if true. Use exact stakeholder groups once only, such as product, security, data, or client teams.","citation":"stakeholder_management 39/88 (44.3%); management_signals_weak true; senior_manager 3%, manager 1%"},{"theme":"Mentoring and design guidance as limited player-coach evidence","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"There is some player-coach behavior, but formal people management is rare. Mentoring can help differentiate if the CV clearly supports it.","ats_guidance":"Mention 'mentoring' or 'technical guidance' once or twice only if true. Do not repeat manager-language across the CV.","citation":"player_coach 38%; mentoring 18/88 (20.5%); hiring 2/88 (2.3%); performance_management 2/88 (2.3%)"}]}],"key_achievement_archetypes":[{"rank":1,"archetype":"End-to-end enterprise AI architecture delivered into production","what_it_proves":"Proves the core category fit: architecture ownership plus delivery, not concept work alone.","pain_points_addressed":["need to solve complex enterprise architecture problems end-to-end","integrate ai and data components into existing enterprise systems","guide implementation from target architecture to production rollout"],"metrics_to_include":["latency reduction","throughput or concurrency","adoption across teams or customers","time-to-production","availability or error-rate improvement"],"story_format_guidance":"Use ARIS: Architecture challenge, design decisions, implementation path, shipped outcome. Make the design choice explicit, then quantify the production result.","citation":"platform_design 87/88 (98.9%); valued evidence: architecture 20, delivery 19; success metrics include performance 5 and production-grade delivery 2"},{"rank":2,"archetype":"Agentic or RAG system with governance and evaluation controls","what_it_proves":"Shows modern GenAI architecture depth with the production safeguards this category values.","pain_points_addressed":["build secure, scalable AI agents connected to external systems","apply strong security to agent and MCP integrations","deliver trustworthy retrieval-grounded workflows"],"metrics_to_include":["quality or accuracy lift","hallucination or failure-rate reduction","policy or safety incident reduction","evaluation coverage","retrieval relevance or response quality"],"story_format_guidance":"Use STAR with risk emphasis: situation and trust constraints, technical approach for agents/RAG/guardrails, measured quality or safety outcome, and deployment scope.","citation":"agents_orchestration 34/88 (38.6%); rag 25/88 (28.4%); guardrails_governance 33/88 (37.5%); evaluation_quality 18/88 (20.5%)"},{"rank":3,"archetype":"Complex integration into APIs, microservices, and enterprise data estates","what_it_proves":"Demonstrates the category's difference from generic GenAI roles: integration architecture inside real enterprise systems.","pain_points_addressed":["integrate ai and data components into java/spring-based microservices","optimize relational and nosql data access and caching for performance","connect AI services to existing APIs and platform boundaries"],"metrics_to_include":["API latency","data pipeline throughput","cache hit rate","service reliability","integration lead time"],"story_format_guidance":"Use STAR. Emphasize the legacy or distributed constraint, the integration pattern chosen, and the measurable operational improvement.","citation":"microservices 12/88 (13.6%); apis 10/88 (11.4%); data pipelines 15/88 (17.0%); pain points include Java/Spring integration and data access optimization (2 mentions each)"},{"rank":4,"archetype":"Cloud modernization or multi-cloud architecture improvement","what_it_proves":"Shows ability to improve existing environments, reduce risk, and scale AI-enabled platforms pragmatically.","pain_points_addressed":["need to scale cloud platforms for large enterprise environments","need to improve existing architectures and algorithms","reduce architectural risk and technical debt while adding AI capability"],"metrics_to_include":["cost reduction","scalability improvement","deployment frequency","infrastructure efficiency","risk or debt reduction"],"story_format_guidance":"Use ARIS. Start with platform constraints or debt, show the target-state architecture, then quantify operational or cost impact.","citation":"cloud_preference: multi_cloud 29%, Azure 15%, AWS 11%; valued evidence: scale 15, cost 7; success metrics include scalability 3, technical debt 2, architectural risks 2, modernization opportunities 2"},{"rank":5,"archetype":"Technical guidance and cross-functional architecture translation","what_it_proves":"Adds player-coach credibility without overstating formal management scope.","pain_points_addressed":["guide team members through AI integration patterns and code quality","align engineering, security, product, and stakeholders around architecture decisions","turn architecture into delivery standards and implementation guidance"],"metrics_to_include":["number of teams enabled","delivery acceleration","defect reduction","review turnaround","standard adoption"],"story_format_guidance":"Use STAR. Focus on the technical leadership mechanism such as standards, reviews, or mentoring, then quantify delivery or quality impact rather than team-size prestige.","citation":"communication 67/88 (76.1%); collaboration 56/88 (63.6%); stakeholder_management 39/88 (44.3%); mentoring 18/88 (20.5%); player_coach 38%"}],"role_weighting_guidance":{"highest_weight_roles":["Roles with explicit architecture ownership, especially AI Architect, AI Solution Architect, Solutions Architect, or equivalent senior technical architect roles.","Roles showing end-to-end delivery of AI-enabled platforms, enterprise integrations, distributed systems, or cloud modernization.","Hands-on technical lead roles should be weighted highly when they show architecture decisions plus delivery outcomes, even if the title is not pure 'architect'."],"expand_in_work_history":["Expand roles with architecture proof, production delivery, stakeholder translation, platform design, cloud/system integration, evaluation, governance, or reliability outcomes.","Expand work that shows enterprise consulting or consultancy context when true, because consulting/consultancy signals recur in 20 roles combined and solution-architecture titles dominate.","Expand roles where non-AI systems experience maps cleanly to distributed systems, APIs, microservices, data platforms, or resilience patterns, then bridge that work to later AI architecture."],"compress_in_work_history":["Compress roles that are mostly people management, generic delivery management, research, or isolated model experimentation without production architecture.","Compress shallow tool-only roles that cannot show ownership of architecture, integration, or measurable deployment outcomes.","Compress early roles with limited relevance once 2-4 strong architecture roles are established."],"how_to_frame_non_ai_experience":["Frame prior backend, platform, cloud, distributed systems, or data engineering work as the foundation for current AI architecture; emphasize service boundaries, resilience, performance, integration, and modernization.","Translate non-AI architecture experience into adjacent evidence such as APIs, microservices, CI/CD, Kubernetes, MLOps-like operational discipline, or enterprise target-state design.","Do not force non-AI roles into GenAI language; instead show continuity from enterprise systems architecture to production AI rollout."],"citations":["title_families: solutions_architect 50%, ai_architect 37%","platform_design 87/88 (98.9%)","market_context: consulting 17, consultancy 3","valued evidence: architecture 20, delivery 19, scale 15","requires_phd 0/88 (0.0%), research_heavy 0/88 (0.0%)"]},"language_and_tone":{"recommended_tone":"architect","formality":"high","preferred_vocabulary":["architecture","solution design","platform design","enterprise integration","production delivery","guardrails","evaluation","reliability","scalability","target architecture","technical roadmap","cross-functional","stakeholder alignment","modernization"],"avoid_vocabulary":["visionary","thought leader","AI evangelist","ninja","guru","best-in-class","full-stack","people manager","P&L owner","research-driven","published"],"citations":["platform_design 87/88 (98.9%)","communication 67/88 (76.1%), collaboration 56/88 (63.6%), stakeholder_management 39/88 (44.3%)","management signals weak: hiring 2/88 (2.3%), performance_management 2/88 (2.3%), budget_pnl 0/88 (0.0%)","requires_phd 0/88 (0.0%), research_heavy 0/88 (0.0%)"]},"unsafe_or_weak_framing":{"avoid_claims":["Customer-facing solution architecture unless client interaction is explicit on the CV.","AWS or Azure architecture ownership unless the provider is named explicitly in prior work.","DevOps, infrastructure, or platform ownership unless supported by concrete deployment responsibility.","Full-stack delivery if the CV mainly shows backend, platform, or architecture work.","Direct public-sector delivery, smart-city, or government deployment claims unless evidenced.","German C1, Polish, or other native-language claims unless explicitly shown.","Hands-on ownership of GDPR, DSGVO, EU AI Act, or responsible-AI programs unless the CV proves delivery scope.","Formal people management, hiring, org building, budget, or direct-report ownership unless explicitly evidenced."],"buzzword_patterns":["Long undifferentiated tool lists without architecture outcomes.","Generic 'LLM expert' or 'GenAI specialist' wording with no production, governance, or integration proof.","Leadership-heavy language that does not show mentoring, stakeholder translation, or architecture decisions.","Cloud badge stacking when multi-cloud or provider-neutral architecture is the safer truth."],"title_inflation_risks":["Inflating technical lead or senior engineer roles into director or head titles.","Using 'Chief' or 'VP' language in a category where senior IC and player-coach signals dominate.","Using 'manager' framing by default when manager roles are only 1% and senior_manager roles 3%."],"research_framing_risks":["Do not add research, publication, or PhD framing as a positive signal in this category.","Do not describe experimentation alone as category fit; convert it into architecture, delivery, evaluation, and governance evidence or omit it."],"domain_or_region_risks":["Do not imply consulting, enterprise SaaS, or public-sector depth unless the CV shows those sectors explicitly.","Do not imply remote-global breadth or multilingual fluency beyond what the CV supports.","Do not imply region-specific compliance leadership from isolated exposure."],"citations":["deep_analysis unsafe_claims_top includes customer-facing, AWS ownership, DevOps ownership, full-stack, public-sector, German C1, DSGVO/EU AI Act ownership","senior_ic 79%, player_coach 38%, senior_manager 3%, manager 1%","hiring 2/88 (2.3%), org_building 10/88 (11.4%), budget_pnl 0/88 (0.0%)","requires_phd 0/88 (0.0%), research_heavy 0/88 (0.0%)","native_language_requirements: German 3, Polish 1, English 1"]},"evidence_ledger":[{"recommendation":"Anchor the CV around hands-on architecture and production delivery rather than executive leadership.","support":["platform_design 87/88 (98.9%)","senior_ic 79%, ic 49%, player_coach 38%, manager 1%","valued evidence: architecture 20, delivery 19"],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Treat communication, collaboration, and stakeholder translation as core signals, but keep management claims narrow.","support":["communication 67/88 (76.1%)","collaboration 56/88 (63.6%)","stakeholder_management 39/88 (44.3%)","hiring 2/88 (2.3%), performance_management 2/88 (2.3%)"],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Use agentic systems, guardrails, governance, and RAG as differentiators when explicitly evidenced.","support":["agents_orchestration 34/88 (38.6%)","guardrails_governance 33/88 (37.5%)","rag 25/88 (28.4%)","evaluation_quality 18/88 (20.5%)"],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Do not overfit the CV around one tool, cloud, or language because the technical stack is fragmented.","support":["highest hard skill is python 29/88 (33.0%); programming_languages required python 31/88 (35.2%)","vector databases 21/88 (23.9%), mlops 17/88 (19.3%), kubernetes 16/88 (18.2%), langchain 20/88 (22.7%)","cloud_preference: multi_cloud 29%, Azure 15%, AWS 11%"],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Weight enterprise integration and modernization stories heavily; this category differs from adjacent AI roles by expecting AI to fit existing systems and architecture constraints.","support":["microservices 12/88 (13.6%), apis 10/88 (11.4%), data pipelines 15/88 (17.0%)","pain points include Java/Spring integration, data access optimization, enterprise architecture problems, and cloud scaling","valued evidence: scale 15, reliability 11, cost 7"],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Keep research, publication, PhD, and formal people-management framing inside risk controls rather than positive positioning.","support":["requires_phd 0/88 (0.0%)","research_heavy 0/88 (0.0%)","budget_pnl 0/88 (0.0%), hiring 2/88 (2.3%), performance_management 2/88 (2.3%)"],"confidence":"high"} 		,{"recommendation":"Use ATS repetition selectively: strongest 4-6 keywords should be architecture, production delivery, agents, guardrails/governance, RAG, and enterprise integration when true.","support":["platform_design 87/88 (98.9%)","agents_orchestration 34/88 (38.6%)","guardrails_governance 33/88 (37.5%)","rag 25/88 (28.4%)","communication 67/88 (76.1%) and collaboration 56/88 (63.6%) support integration/stakeholder wording"],"confidence":"medium"} 	,{"recommendation":"Use cloud-provider keywords conservatively; prefer provider-neutral architecture unless the CV has named delivery on that platform.","support":["cloud_preference: multi_cloud 29% exceeds Azure 15% and AWS 11%","deep-analysis unsafe claims flag AWS ownership if not shown explicitly"],"confidence":"high"} 	,{"recommendation":"Mentoring can be presented as limited player-coach evidence, but not as broad team management.","support":["player_coach 38%","mentoring 18/88 (20.5%)","org_building 10/88 (11.4%), hiring 2/88 (2.3%)"],"confidence":"medium"} 	,{"recommendation":"This category is distinct from research-heavy AI roles because hiring evidence rewards shipped architecture, reliability, evaluation, governance, and integration over model novelty.","support":["valued evidence: architecture 20, delivery 19, reliability 11, evaluation 11, governance 10","requires_phd 0/88 (0.0%), research_heavy 0/88 (0.0%)"],"confidence":"high"}] }
