./data/eval/blueprints/debug/ai_architect_global/20260415_170024/attempt_01_initial_raw_output.txt:1:{"meta":{"category_id":"ai_architect_global","category_name":"AI Architect — Global/Remote","macro_family":"ai_architect","priority":"primary_target","confidence":"high","total_jobs":88,"deep_analysis_count":20,"low_sample_mode":false,"noisy_title_mode":false,"uncertainty_note":"Evidence is strong for this category (88 jobs, 20 deep analyses). Precision is good at the role-archetype level, but provider, language, domain, and compliance claims still require explicit CV proof because no single hard skill exceeds 60%."},"category_signature":{"one_sentence_summary":"A top-third CV for this category should read as a senior architect profile that proves enterprise AI platform design, production delivery, secure integration, and stakeholder translation more than pure management or model research.","distinctive_signals":["Architect-heavy and delivery-heavy: platform design appears in 87/88 roles (98.9%), while deep-analysis evidence most often rewards architecture (20/20) and delivery (19/20).","The role is primarily senior IC with player-coach edges, not people management: senior_ic 79%, IC 49%, player_coach 38%, hiring 2/88 (2.3%), performance management 2/88 (2.3%), org building 10/88 (11.4%).","GenAI architecture is production-oriented rather than research-oriented: agents/orchestration 34/88 (38.6%), guardrails/governance 33/88 (37.5%), RAG 25/88 (28.4%), evaluation/quality 18/88 (20.5%), requires_phd 0/88 (0.0%), research_heavy 0/88 (0.0%)."],"citations":["Platform design 87/88 (98.9%); architecture valued evidence 20/20; delivery valued evidence 19/20.","Senior_ic 79%; IC 49%; player_coach 38%; hiring 2/88 (2.3%); org_building 10/88 (11.4%).","Agents/orchestration 34/88 (38.6%); guardrails/governance 33/88 (37.5%); RAG 25/88 (28.4%); evaluation/quality 18/88 (20.5%); requires_phd 0/88 (0.0%); research_heavy 0/88 (0.0%)."]},"headline_pattern":{"recommended_structure":"[AI Solution Architect / AI Architect] | Enterprise AI Platforms, Agents, Integration & Governance | [Cloud/provider only if explicitly evidenced]","safe_title_families":["Solutions Architect","AI Architect"],"safe_title_variants":["AI Solution Architect","Generative AI Solution Architect","AI Architect","AI Software Architect"],"avoid_title_variants":["Head of AI","Director of AI","VP AI","AI Research Architect","Engineering Manager"],"evidence_first_rules":["Default to architect-family titles because title families skew to solutions_architect 50% and ai_architect 37%; do not inflate into manager/executive labels when manager signals are minimal.","Name provider-specific titles only if the CV shows delivery on that provider; Azure and AWS each appear in just 14/88 roles (15.9%), so cloud branding is supporting evidence, not a safe default.","Use agent, RAG, governance, or evaluation keywords in the headline only when shipped work exists: agents/orchestration 34/88 (38.6%), guardrails/governance 33/88 (37.5%), RAG 25/88 (28.4%), evaluation/quality 18/88 (20.5%).","Do not anchor the headline around one technical keyword as if it is universal; no hard skill reaches 60%, and Python leads at only 31/88 (35.2%)."],"citations":["Title families: solutions_architect 50%, ai_architect 37%, tech_lead 1%.","Role scope: senior_ic 79%, senior_manager 3%, manager 1%.","Azure 14/88 (15.9%), AWS 14/88 (15.9%), multi_cloud 29%.","Python 31/88 (35.2%); agents/orchestration 34/88 (38.6%); RAG 25/88 (28.4%)."]},"tagline_profile_angle":{"positioning_angle":["Position as a senior enterprise AI architect who turns target-state designs into production systems.","Position as a stakeholder-facing translator for secure GenAI rollout, but keep the profile hands-on enough to show delivery credibility."],"foreground":["Architecture proof, end-to-end delivery, enterprise integration, security/guardrails, evaluation, scale, and stakeholder translation."],"avoid":["Executive org-building language, research-led framing, provider-specific authority without evidence, and generic 'AI strategy' wording without shipped systems."],"safe_positioning":["Senior individual contributor or architect-first player-coach who designs platforms, aligns stakeholders, and stays close to implementation.","Consulting-friendly architect who can modernize existing estates as well as lead greenfield AI initiatives."],"unsafe_positioning":["People manager, hiring owner, or org builder by default.","Research-oriented AI specialist, publication-led profile, or PhD-style positioning.","Customer-facing solution architect, AWS/Azure authority, or compliance owner unless the CV shows those exact responsibilities."],"citations":["Communication 67/88 (76.1%), collaboration 56/88 (63.6%), stakeholder management 39/88 (44.3%).","IC 49%, player_coach 38%, manager 1%, hiring 2/88 (2.3%), org_building 10/88 (11.4%).","Requires_phd 0/88 (0.0%), research_heavy 0/88 (0.0%)."]},"core_competency_themes":[{"section_name":"Architecture Proof","themes":[{"theme":"Enterprise AI platform and solution architecture","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This category is defined by architecture ownership more than coding-language specialization. Show target-state design, reference architecture choices, service boundaries, and platform rollout because platform design appears in 87/88 roles (98.9%) and architecture is the most valued evidence type in 20/20 deep analyses.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: 'AI solution architect', 'AI architect', 'solution architecture', 'platform design', 'enterprise architecture' with 2-3 mentions across headline/profile/experience/skills. Secondary: 'target architecture', 'reference architecture', 'technical roadmap' with 1-2 mentions. Niche terms once only.","citation":"Platform design 87/88 (98.9%); architecture valued evidence 20/20; title families solutions_architect 50%, ai_architect 37%."},{"theme":"Greenfield plus modernization delivery","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"The market favors architects who can both create new AI capabilities and improve existing systems. Show cases where you designed greenfield AI services and also modernized legacy or current-state platforms, because both modes appear together far more often than either alone.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: 'greenfield', 'modernization', 'platform rollout', 'production delivery' with 2-3 mentions. Secondary: 'technical debt', 'architectural risk', 'migration' with 1-2 mentions. Niche transformation labels once only.","citation":"Greenfield_split: both 42, optimization 6, greenfield 7; delivery valued evidence 19/20; success metrics include identifying technical debt 2/20 and identifying architectural risks 2/20."},{"theme":"Enterprise integration and service-boundary design","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"This category sits closer to enterprise systems integration than pure model work. Show how AI capabilities connected into existing APIs, microservices, data services, or business systems, especially where architecture decisions reduced coupling or improved operability.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: 'enterprise integration', 'microservices', 'APIs', 'service boundaries' with 2-3 mentions. Secondary: 'event-driven', 'distributed systems', 'Java/Spring integration' with 1-2 mentions. Niche broker/framework names once only.","citation":"Microservices 12/88 (13.6%); APIs 10/88 (11.4%); pain points include integrating AI/data components into Java/Spring microservices (count 2) and solving enterprise architecture problems end-to-end (count 1)."}]},{"section_name":"GenAI Production Stack","themes":[{"theme":"Agents and orchestration connected to enterprise systems","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"The category is distinctly stronger on agentic system design than on isolated prompt work. Show agent workflows, tool or system connectivity, routing/orchestration, and production controls around those flows.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: 'agents', 'orchestration', 'agent workflows', 'tool integration' with 2-3 mentions. Secondary: 'MCP', 'workflow orchestration', 'multi-step automation' with 1-2 mentions. Niche protocol or framework names once only and only if true.","citation":"Agents/orchestration 34/88 (38.6%); prompt_engineering 15/88 (17.0%); pain point: build secure, scalable AI agents that connect to external systems through MCP (count 2)."},{"theme":"RAG, vector search, and evaluation loops","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Top profiles show retrieval and quality control as architectural components, not just model features. Demonstrate how retrieval, chunking/indexing choices, vector search, and evaluation gates improved answer quality or operational trust.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: 'RAG', 'vector search', 'vector databases', 'evaluation' with 2-3 mentions. Secondary: 'retrieval pipelines', 'grounding', 'quality metrics' with 1-2 mentions. Niche libraries such as LangChain/LangGraph/LlamaIndex once only unless they are central to multiple roles.","citation":"RAG 25/88 (28.4%); vector_search 19/88 (21.6%); vector databases 21/88 (23.9%); evaluation/quality 18/88 (20.5%); LangChain 20/88 (22.7%); LangGraph 9/88 (10.2%)."},{"theme":"Hands-on implementation depth without pretending one stack is universal","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"Hands-on credibility helps, but the market does not converge on one universal technical keyword. Use Python, LangChain, cloud SDKs, or model frameworks only when they are genuinely evidenced, and keep architecture outcomes ahead of tool lists.","ats_guidance":"If true, use one implementation stack as supporting evidence: strongest keywords can be 'Python', 'LangChain', 'MLOps', 'Kubernetes' with 2-3 mentions only when central to the record. Secondary cloud/framework keywords 1-2 mentions. Niche frameworks once only.","citation":"No hard skill reaches 60%; Python 31/88 (35.2%), LangChain 20/88 (22.7%), MLOps 17/88 (19.3%), Kubernetes 16/88 (18.2%)."}]},{"section_name":"Productionization And Control","themes":[{"theme":"Guardrails, governance, and secure rollout","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Employers want architecture that is safe to run in production, not just impressive in demos. Show governance controls, security decisions, human-review or policy layers, and how those reduced risk in enterprise settings.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: 'guardrails', 'governance', 'security', 'responsible AI' with 2-3 mentions. Secondary: 'policy controls', 'access control', 'compliance' with 1-2 mentions. Region-specific regulations once only and only if explicitly delivered.","citation":"Guardrails/governance 33/88 (37.5%); security 3/88 (3.4%); responsible AI 6/88 (6.8%); GDPR 8/88 (9.1%); pain point: apply strong application security to agent and MCP integrations (count 2)."},{"theme":"Operationalization with MLOps, pipelines, CI/CD, and platform tooling","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"The category rewards architects who can carry designs into deployable operating models. Show deployment pipelines, model/app release controls, observability setup, or platform automation when those were part of your remit, but avoid claiming full infrastructure ownership if the CV does not support it.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: 'MLOps', 'CI/CD', 'data pipelines', 'Kubernetes' with 2-3 mentions. Secondary: 'observability', 'monitoring', 'deployment automation' with 1-2 mentions. Specific tooling once only unless it appears in multiple roles.","citation":"MLOps 17/88 (19.3%); Kubernetes 16/88 (18.2%); data pipelines 15/88 (17.0%); CI/CD 11/88 (12.5%); observability tools each appear at 1.1-2.3%."},{"theme":"Performance, scale, cost, and maintainability outcomes","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"Architecture claims are stronger when tied to operating results. Quantify latency, throughput, reliability, scalability, cost efficiency, maintainability gains, or debt reduction because deep analyses repeatedly reward these outcomes.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: 'performance', 'scalability', 'reliability', 'cost optimization' with 2-3 mentions in experience bullets. Secondary: 'maintainability', 'technical debt reduction', 'production-grade' with 1-2 mentions. Metric labels should appear directly in bullets, not just the skills section.","citation":"Valued evidence types: scale 15/20, reliability 11/20, cost 7/20; success metrics: performance 5/20, scalability 3/20, security 3/20, maintainability 2/20, production-grade delivery 2/20."}]},{"section_name":"Stakeholder Translation","themes":[{"theme":"Communication and cross-functional collaboration","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This category is unusually explicit about soft-skill evidence because architects must align product, engineering, and business stakeholders around delivery tradeoffs. Show concrete collaboration settings, decisions influenced, and translated tradeoffs, not generic soft-skill adjectives.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: 'communication', 'cross-functional collaboration', 'stakeholder alignment' with 2-3 mentions across summary and experience. Secondary: 'workshops', 'requirements translation', 'decision framing' with 1-2 mentions. Generic soft-skill lists should be brief.","citation":"Communication 67/88 (76.1%); collaboration 56/88 (63.6%); stakeholder management 39/88 (44.3%)."},{"theme":"Consulting-style stakeholder translation in enterprise environments","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Compared with adjacent AI roles, this category leans more toward consulting-flavored architecture translation. Show client-facing or stakeholder-facing architecture work, proposal-to-delivery continuity, or enterprise program alignment only when explicitly evidenced.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: 'enterprise stakeholders', 'solution workshops', 'architecture consulting', 'client alignment' with 2-3 mentions. Secondary: 'remote-first collaboration', 'hybrid delivery', 'advisory' with 1-2 mentions. Do not use customer-facing wording if the CV lacks it.","citation":"Domain context: consulting 17, consultancy 3, enterprise_saas 5, enterprise 2; remote_first 13, hybrid 14; stakeholder management 39/88 (44.3%)."},{"theme":"Mentoring and technical guidance without people-management inflation","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"Player-coach behavior can help when real, but people leadership is not the center of gravity. Show mentoring, design reviews, or pattern guidance if you have it, and keep hiring/performance-management claims out unless explicitly evidenced.","ats_guidance":"If true, use 'mentoring', 'technical leadership', and 'design guidance' 1-2 times in experience. Keep them secondary to architecture and delivery. Avoid repeated management keywords unless the role truly owned people outcomes.","citation":"Player_coach 38%; mentoring 18/88 (20.5%); leadership 21/88 (23.9%); hiring 2/88 (2.3%); performance management 2/88 (2.3%)."}]}],"key_achievement_archetypes":[{"rank":1,"archetype":"Designed the target architecture and shipped a production enterprise AI platform","what_it_proves":"Shows the core hire signal for this category: architecture ownership tied directly to delivery, not slideware.","pain_points_addressed":["need to solve complex enterprise architecture problems end-to-end","need to scale cloud platforms for large enterprise environments"],"metrics_to_include":["business units or tenants served","production environments launched","time from design to production","uptime or SLO attainment","deployment frequency or release lead time"],"story_format_guidance":"Use STAR or ARIS with the architecture constraint first, then the design decision, then the production outcome. Name the platform scope and quantify rollout, not just the technology stack.","citation":"Platform design 87/88 (98.9%); architecture valued evidence 20/20; delivery valued evidence 19/20; scale valued evidence 15/20."},{"rank":2,"archetype":"Integrated AI agents or RAG capabilities into existing enterprise systems securely","what_it_proves":"Shows that you can connect GenAI to real business systems with workable integration, security, and operational boundaries.","pain_points_addressed":["build secure, scalable ai agents that can connect to external systems through mcp","integrate ai and data components into java/spring-based microservices","apply strong application security to agent and mcp integrations"],"metrics_to_include":["number of systems or tools integrated","workflow success rate","latency per step or end-to-end latency","security findings reduced","manual effort removed or cycle time reduced"],"story_format_guidance":"Start with the enterprise system constraint, then explain the integration pattern, control model, and rollout result. Make security and operability part of the story, not an afterthought.","citation":"Agents/orchestration 34/88 (38.6%); RAG 25/88 (28.4%); guardrails/governance 33/88 (37.5%); microservices 12/88 (13.6%); APIs 10/88 (11.4%)."},{"rank":3,"archetype":"Built evaluation, guardrails, and governance into production GenAI delivery","what_it_proves":"Demonstrates production maturity and risk control, which separates credible architect profiles from prototype-heavy ones.","pain_points_addressed":["apply strong application security to agent and mcp integrations","need to solve complex enterprise architecture problems end-to-end"],"metrics_to_include":["evaluation pass rates","error or hallucination reduction","policy coverage","incident rate reduction","auditability or review-cycle time"],"story_format_guidance":"Frame the before-state risk, then the control architecture, then the measurable improvement in trust, safety, or production readiness. Use concrete quality and reliability numbers wherever possible.","citation":"Guardrails/governance 33/88 (37.5%); evaluation/quality 18/88 (20.5%); governance valued evidence 10/20; reliability valued evidence 11/20."},{"rank":4,"archetype":"Improved performance, scalability, cost, or maintainability of AI and data architecture","what_it_proves":"Shows you are not just a builder of new systems but an optimizer of enterprise architecture under production constraints.","pain_points_addressed":["optimize relational and nosql data access and caching for performance","need to improve existing architectures and algorithms"],"metrics_to_include":["latency reduction","throughput increase","infra or token cost reduction","cache hit rate","availability improvement","maintenance effort reduced"],"story_format_guidance":"Lead with the bottleneck, then the architectural change, then the measured result. Favor percentage improvements and absolute throughput or cost numbers over generic claims of optimization.","citation":"Scale valued evidence 15/20; reliability valued evidence 11/20; cost valued evidence 7/20; success metrics: performance 5/20, scalability 3/20, maintainability 2/20."},{"rank":5,"archetype":"Aligned stakeholders and coached engineers through enterprise AI rollout","what_it_proves":"Shows consulting-grade translation skill and player-coach effectiveness without overstating people management.","pain_points_addressed":["guide team members through ai integration patterns and code quality","need to solve complex enterprise architecture problems end-to-end"],"metrics_to_include":["teams enabled","workshops or design reviews led","adoption across squads","decision lead time","delivery acceleration after alignment"],"story_format_guidance":"Describe the stakeholder conflict or delivery ambiguity, then the alignment mechanism, then the delivery outcome. Keep the emphasis on technical translation and execution, not abstract leadership language.","citation":"Communication 67/88 (76.1%); collaboration 56/88 (63.6%); stakeholder management 39/88 (44.3%); player_coach 38%; mentoring 18/88 (20.5%)."}],"role_weighting_guidance":{"highest_weight_roles":["Architecture-heavy roles titled around Solution Architect or AI Architect.","Senior technical roles where architecture, delivery, and stakeholder translation all appear in the scope.","Tech lead roles only when they clearly show platform design and cross-functional architecture leadership rather than pure team management."],"expand_in_work_history":["Roles with target architecture ownership, platform design, or system-integration decisions.","Roles with shipped AI/GenAI delivery, especially agents, RAG, governance, or evaluation in production.","Roles showing enterprise modernization, distributed systems, cloud rollout, or measurable scale/reliability outcomes.","Roles showing stakeholder workshops, client alignment, or technical coaching when explicitly evidenced."],"compress_in_work_history":["Pure line-management scope with little architecture evidence.","Research-only or experimentation-heavy work without production delivery.","Generic full-stack, frontend, or unrelated implementation detail that does not support architecture credibility.","Early roles that do not contribute to distributed systems, platform design, or enterprise delivery narrative."],"how_to_frame_non_ai_experience":["Translate non-AI architecture work into service-boundary design, integration architecture, distributed systems, resilience, and modernization foundations for AI delivery.","Use cloud/platform history to prove production rigor, scalability, security, and rollout discipline before introducing AI-specific work.","Frame backend or platform engineering experience as the technical substrate for later AI architecture, especially where APIs, microservices, eventing, or data pipelines were involved."],"citations":["Seniority: senior_ic 79%, mid_ic 2%, senior_manager 3%, manager 1%.","Role scope: IC 49%, player_coach 38%, manager 1%.","Management signals remain weak: hiring 2/88 (2.3%), performance management 2/88 (2.3%), org_building 10/88 (11.4%).","Architecture valued evidence 20/20; delivery 19/20; scale 15/20."]},"language_and_tone":{"recommended_tone":"architect","formality":"high","preferred_vocabulary":["solution architecture","AI architecture","platform design","target architecture","production rollout","enterprise integration","guardrails","evaluation","scalability","reliability","modernization","stakeholder alignment"],"avoid_vocabulary":["visionary","thought leader","evangelist","AI guru","Head of AI","research scientist","full-stack expert","cloud expert"],"citations":["The market centers on architecture and delivery: architecture 20/20, delivery 19/20, platform design 87/88 (98.9%).","Soft-skill emphasis is real but operational: communication 67/88 (76.1%), collaboration 56/88 (63.6%), stakeholder management 39/88 (44.3%).","Research-heavy framing is unsupported: requires_phd 0/88 (0.0%), research_heavy 0/88 (0.0%)."]},"unsafe_or_weak_framing":{"avoid_claims":["Hiring, performance management, or org-building ownership unless the CV shows explicit scope and outcomes.","AWS, Azure, or multi-cloud architecture authority unless those platforms are named in delivered work.","Customer-facing solution architecture, workshops, or business facilitation if the CV does not show direct stakeholder interaction.","DevOps or infrastructure ownership if the record supports architecture collaboration rather than platform operations ownership.","Public-sector, administration, mobility-data, or smart-city delivery unless explicitly evidenced.","GDPR, DSGVO, EU AI Act, or broader compliance-program ownership unless the CV shows hands-on delivery against those controls.","Full-stack delivery if the evidence is mainly backend, platform, or architecture work."],"buzzword_patterns":["'Agentic AI leader' without shipped agent workflows, external integrations, or controls.","'AI strategy' without architecture decisions, delivery scope, or production results.","'Responsible AI expert' without governance, security, evaluation, or policy evidence.","'Multi-cloud architect' without named Azure/AWS delivery examples.","Long framework lists that do not tie to architecture outcomes."],"title_inflation_risks":["Inflating architect profiles into Director, VP, or Head titles despite manager signals of only 1-3%.","Using Engineering Manager or org-leader branding when the category is predominantly senior IC/player-coach.","Using research-oriented titles for a market with 0/88 PhD requirement and 0/88 research-heavy signal."],"research_framing_risks":["Do not foreground publications, academic depth, or model research as the profile center; this market is delivery-led.","Do not present experimentation alone as proof of fit when architecture, integration, and production outcomes are the valued evidence."],"domain_or_region_risks":["Do not claim German, Polish, or other language capability unless explicitly evidenced; native-language requirements appear but are not category-wide.","Do not overfit the CV to public sector, government deployment, or on-prem/hybrid regulated environments unless shown in the record.","Do not imply direct compliance-program ownership from light governance signals alone.","Do not imply region-specific legal expertise from one-off references to GDPR or EU AI Act."],"citations":["Unsafe claims from deep analysis include unsupported German C1, AWS ownership, customer-facing architecture, DevOps ownership, full-stack delivery, DSGVO/EU AI Act ownership, public-sector delivery, and on-prem government deployment.","Management evidence is limited: hiring 2/88 (2.3%), performance management 2/88 (2.3%), org_building 10/88 (11.4%).","Native-language requirements in deep analysis: German 3, Polish 1, English 1.","Governance/compliance mentions are present but not dominant: GDPR 8/88 (9.1%), responsible AI 6/88 (6.8%), EU AI Act 2/88 (2.3%)."]},"evidence_ledger":[{"recommendation":"Lead with architect branding and architecture proof, not manager branding.","support":["Title families skew to solutions_architect 50% and ai_architect 37%.","Platform design appears in 87/88 roles (98.9%).","Senior_ic is 79%, while manager is 1% and senior_manager is 3%."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Center production delivery stories that connect architecture decisions to shipped enterprise outcomes.","support":["Architecture is the top valued evidence type in 20/20 deep analyses.","Delivery is the second-highest valued evidence type in 19/20 deep analyses.","Success metrics repeatedly mention performance, scalability, reliability, maintainability, and production-grade delivery."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Use agents, RAG, evaluation, and guardrails as differentiators when they were delivered in production.","support":["Agents/orchestration 34/88 (38.6%).","Guardrails/governance 33/88 (37.5%).","RAG 25/88 (28.4%) and evaluation/quality 18/88 (20.5%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Do not build the CV around one supposedly universal technical keyword.","support":["No hard skill reaches 60% in this category.","Python leads at 31/88 (35.2%), while vector databases are 21/88 (23.9%) and LangChain is 20/88 (22.7%).","Azure and AWS each appear in just 14/88 roles (15.9%), so provider branding is supporting evidence, not a safe default."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Treat stakeholder translation and consulting fluency as important, but keep them tied to concrete delivery evidence.","support":["Communication 67/88 (76.1%), collaboration 56/88 (63.6%), stakeholder management 39/88 (44.3%).","Consulting and consultancy appear 20 times in market context.","Remote-first 13 and hybrid 14 indicate distributed collaboration is common."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Keep people management, research framing, and compliance ownership out unless explicitly evidenced.","support":["Hiring 2/88 (2.3%), performance management 2/88 (2.3%), org_building 10/88 (11.4%).","Requires_phd 0/88 (0.0%) and research_heavy 0/88 (0.0%).","GDPR is only 8/88 (9.1%) and EU AI Act only 2/88 (2.3%), so compliance ownership is not a safe default claim."],"confidence":"high"} 
./data/eval/raw/head_of_ai_global/jd_texts/53_everai_senior_devops_engineer_full_remote_hungary.md:10:Our Vision & Products🚀 EverAI — Building the Future of AI CompanionshipOne of the Top 15 Largest & Fastest-Growing AI Companies in the World35+ Million Users in 2 years — Help Us Reach 100M first, 500M nextAt EverAI, we’re shaping what it means to connect with AI. With 35+ millionusers and counting, we're not just building products — we're creating entirelynew categories.Our flagship product is the world’s largest AI girlfriend/boyfriend platform,redefining relationships for millions. It is governed by our proprietarymoderation system, EverGuard — an internal AI designed to ensure everything webuild is safe, ethical, and human-first.And we’re only just getting started!Our TeamWe are an enthusiastic, passionate and hardworking team of 70 people. Ourfounding team has strong entrepreneurial experience building and scaling webproducts from 0 to IPO.Alexis Soulopoulos [CEO] * 10+ years in Tech Executive Leadership * Co-Founder Mad Paws Holdings (from 0 to IPO) * Forbes 30 under 30 + Deloitte TechFast50 ’22 & ‘23 Michael Monin [Co-founder & CTO] * 10+ years as CTO / COO (web2/web3), 1+ year in AI/LLM * Serial-entrepreneur: MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue) and Zipchat (AI Chatbot for E-commerce brands) Thomas Lacroix [Co-founder & CMO] * 8+ years in Customer Acquisition & E-commerce Growth * Serial-entrepreneur: Curatible (sold to Blackstone) and MTK Digital (exited / 0->$20m revenue) Maruša Fasano [CFO/Legal] * 25+ years in Finance, Strategy, M&A * Ex-CFO/M&A @Curatible (exited to Blackstone) * Ex-President of the Board @SotremoSA (exited) * Co-founder/CFO @SoftOne (exited) Your RoleOur user base and tech team are expanding rapidly, we are therefore hiring aSenior DevOps Engineer to help us build and scale our platform and support ourengineering teams. You’ll have the opportunity to help define our roadmap andfind the best technical solutions to help our customers. You will also have timeto run some experiments and bring new ideas to the table.Reporting directly to our DevOps Lead, Mate, you will be responsible for: * Interacting with the engineers to provide infrastructure support * Manage, monitor and scale our existing services * Provision infrastructure and platform services through Infrastructure-as-Code, code reviews and testing You will be working with Michael (Co-founder & CTO), along with the Product teamand the Engineering team (web developers, SRE, data scientists).Your QualificationsMust-haves💼 5+ years of experience: * Public cloud, Kubernetes, GitOps * Observability through logs, metrics and tracing * Infrastucture-as-Code, Terraform, Helm * Ability to read and understand application code (Go, Python, shell) * In tech startups or any similarly agile and fast-paced environment 🗣 Strong communication & collaborative skills (perfectly fluent in English)🎯 Goal-oriented, ownership and commitment⚡️ Doer mindset - we are moving fast and need people who can balance execution,planning, and strategy🧢 Humble - willing to learn, open to feedback🫶🏻 User-centricity - you are proud of what you build and you share ourobsession for amazing user experience🍭 #NSFW - you are comfortable building products that are based on uncensoredmodels and contentBonus points * Past experience and/or interest in data science and generative AI (NLP, ML, MLOps, etc.) * Location: you must be able to work within ±4 CET Why EverAI?📈 Exponential Growth: From 35M+ users in 2 years, to 100M next — and 500Mbeyond🚀 Track Record of Category-Creating Innovation: We consistently launchworld-first AI applications — setting the pace, not following it🌍 Global Impact: Top-tier user growth, real-world adoption, and culturalrelevance🧠 Proven Leadership: A senior team that’s launched, scaled, and exited & IPO’dmultiple scale ups — now fully focused on reshaping AI companionship👥 Elite Remote Team: 100% remote and built to win — world-class talent fromTier 1 tech companies, with a culture of ownership, velocity, and radicalcreativity🛡️ Ethical Core: Our AI ecosystem is governed by EverGuard, our proprietary AImoderation technology, ensuring responsible development at scaleWhat we offer✍️ Contract Type: We prefer B2B, but we’re flexible, what matters is long-termcommitment and impact📍 Work From Anywhere: Fully remote. Choose the environment where you do yourbest work🏝️ Paid Time Off: 4 weeks (20 working days) of PTO per year to recharge andreset👨👩👧👦 Annual Gathering: A yearly in-person meetup to connect, brainstorm,and celebrate wins together❤️🩹 Health & Wellness Support: Up to $200 per year for wellbeing expenses +unlimited 1:1 sessions with psychologists and lifestyle experts through OpenUp(also available for up to three family members)🏢 Co-Working Space Budget: Work from a co-working space up to twice per month(35 EUR / 40 USD per visit) to stay inspired and connected📚 Learning Budget: Dedicated funds to support your professional growth:courses, books, conferences, events, or certifications💻 Equipment: Company laptop provided + monitor budget up to $250 for yourworkspace setup⚡ AI Tools Access: Premium access to ChatGPT, Cursor, Hugging Face, and others,to power your ideas and workflows🎯 Top Tier Talent Is Our MultiplierWe’re a fully remote group of A-players from Tier 1 tech, led by an exec teamwho’ve launched, scaled, and exited multiple companies. We move fast, and caredeeply about what we build — and who we build it with.We’re looking for exceptional talent ready to ship & distribute world-first AIproducts at scale, fast, and co-create with us this category-defining business.If that’s you — reach out and apply!💡 External Referral ProgramKnow someone who could be a great fit for this role? You can refer them throughthe EverAI External Referral Program and earn a bonus of up to $2,500 if they’rehired. Submit a referral here.Show more Show less
./data/eval/raw/ai_architect_eea/jd_texts/04_softserve_mlllm_technical_architect.md:10:WE ARESoftServe is a global digital solutions company, headquartered in Austin, Texas,and founded in 1993. With 2,000+ active projects across the USA, Europe, APAC,and LATAM, we deliver meaningful outcomes through bold thinking and deepexpertise. Our people create impactful solutions, drive innovation, andgenuinely enjoy what they do.The AI and Data Science Center of Excellence (CoE) is SoftServe’s premier AI/MLhub, primarily based in Europe. With 130+ experts, including data scientists,research analysts, MLOps engineers, ML and LLM architects, we cover the full AIlifecycle, from problem framing to deployment.In 2024, we delivered 150+ AI projects, including over 100 focused on GenerativeAI, combining scale with measurable impact.We are a 2024 NVIDIA Service Delivery Partner and maintain strong collaborationswith Google Cloud, Amazon, and Microsoft, ensuring our teams always work withcutting-edge tools and technologies.We also lead Gen AI Lab, our internal innovation engine focused on appliedresearch and cross-functional collaboration in Generative AI.In 2025, a key area of innovation is Agentic AI, where we design and deployautonomous, collaborative agent systems capable of addressing complex,real-world challenges at scale for our clients and internally.IF YOU ARE * Educated with a degree in Computer Science or a related field * Experienced in a similar position, including 2+ years of design and implementation of enterprise-scale AI/ML solutions in the AWS cloud using services such as Amazon SageMaker, AWS Bedrock, Amazon Kendra, AWS Glue, AWS Data Pipelines, Amazon Kinesis, Amazon Athena, and Amazon Redshift * Designing sustainable, scalable, and secure architectures, performing trade-off analysis of different architecture tactics and patterns, and applying proven architecture design approaches and methodologies, with a focus on GenAI and LLM-based solutions * Driving project roll-outs from requirements gathering to go-live and continuous improvement * Skilled in designing, building, or operationalizing Agentic AI systems, with hands-on experience leveraging frameworks like Amazon Bedrock Agents to create autonomous and goal-oriented GenAI solutions * Confident in customer-facing tasks related to discovery, assessment, execution, and operations for complex AI/ML/GenAI projects * Driving project roll-outs from requirements gathering to go-live and continuous improvement * Knowledgeable of EKS/ECS platforms and their design patterns for ML workloads * Confident upper-intermediate English speaker * Responsible for AI principles and practices, including model explainability, fairness, and security for GenAI (nice to have) * Experienced in pre-sales, enterprise consulting, or AI/ML advisory roles (would be a plus) AND YOU WANT TO * Engage in a wide scope of AI and ML-related work, from foundational machine learning projects to advanced Generative AI applications * Bring your deep expertise in cloud architecture, DevOps, and MLOps/LLMOps to analyze and recommend enterprise-grade solutions for operationalizing the full spectrum of AI * Develop end-to-end MLOps/LLMOps pipelines on AWS, leveraging an in-depth understanding of the platform, the entire AI lifecycle, and business problems to ensure solutions are delivered efficiently, predictably, and sustainably * Prototype and demonstrate innovative solutions, including proof-of-concepts for diverse AI/ML use cases and specific GenAI applications, for clients in customer environments * Develop assets, accelerators, and reusable components for your practice, covering both established AI/ML methodologies and emerging GenAI and LLMOps space * Communicate use cases, technical requirements, architectural decisions, and expectations clearly with stakeholders at all levels * Guide Engineering and Data Science teams on the production lifecycle of ML systems, including best practices for building, deploying, and monitoring traditional ML models and LLM-powered applications * Educate product teams on best practices for reliably and responsibly putting ML systems into production, including innovative GenAI features TOGETHER WE WILL * Operationalize our clients’ AI solutions, from traditional ML to cutting-edge Generative AI applications, by leveraging best practices in Machine Learning, DevOps, LLMOps, and Solution Architecture * Maintain synergy among Data Scientists, DevOps teams, and ML Engineers to build robust infrastructure, set up efficient processes, productize machine learning and GenAI pipelines, and integrate them seamlessly into existing business environments * Participate in international events, conferences, and workshops to share our expertise and learn from the global AI community * Get certifications in cutting-edge technologies and continuously enhance our skills in the dynamic field of AI * Drive innovation by exploring and implementing novel AI and GenAI solutions that deliver significant business value for our clients * Have the possibility to work with the latest technologies on different projects and internal initiatives * Communicate with the world-leading companies from our logos portfolio * Work as a consultant on different projects with a flexible schedule SoftServe is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants willreceive consideration for employment regardless of race, color, religion, age,sex, nationality, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity andexpression, veteran status, and other protected characteristics under applicablelaw. Let’s put your talents and experience in motion with SoftServe.Show more Show less
